check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nSystem >> System Integrity - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSystem Integrity records events related to violations of integrity to the security subsystem.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00216, SRG-OS-000477-GPOS-00222","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"1124","uuid":"ee7e137f-a43d-43a1-a182-4c96b90412a7","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254332","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254332","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254332","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-254332r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-254332","rule_version":"WN22-AU-000390","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit System - System Integrity failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> System >> Audit System Integrity with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nSystem >> System Integrity - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSystem Integrity records events related to violations of integrity to the security subsystem.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00215, SRG-OS-000471-GPOS-00216, SRG-OS-000477-GPOS-00222","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"6697","uuid":"84b42d2e-2128-499e-b1f0-f76f2ca2664a","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254333","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254333","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254333","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254333r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254333","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000010","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent the display of slide shows on the lock screen.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Control Panel >> Personalization >> Prevent enabling lock screen slide show to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the registry value below. \n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Personalization\\\n\nValue Name: NoLockScreenSlideshow\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Slide shows that are displayed on the lock screen could display sensitive information to unauthorized personnel. Turning off this feature will limit access to the information to a logged-on user.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"7685","uuid":"b90218a4-da05-45af-9056-03f328eabb16","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D053B1CA6A0F90F95B413080D50E63C008C2A894\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must prevent the display of slide shows on the lock screen.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254334","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254334","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254334","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254334r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254334","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000020","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have WDigest Authentication disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide . Set \"WDigest Authentication (disabling may require KB2871997)\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \" SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\Wdigest\\\n\nValue Name:  UseLogonCredential\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When the WDigest Authentication protocol is enabled, plain-text passwords are stored in the Local Security Authority Subsystem Service (LSASS), exposing them to theft. WDigest is disabled by default in Windows Server 2022. This setting ensures this is enforced.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8308","uuid":"837df527-80c9-4e1b-a3a8-d61f8dc52801","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254335","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254335","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254335","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254335r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254335","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000030","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Internet Protocol version 6 (IPv6) source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent IP source routing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting IPv6) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing) to \"Enabled\" with \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\" selected.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip6\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IPv6 source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6508","uuid":"0361f9b6-8eae-4ca0-b5d2-ee6d017a9684","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: ABB7DBB86C1455A0DF149A3E344692003EFC36B6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Internet Protocol version 6 (IPv6) source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent IP source routing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254336","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254336","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254336","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254336r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254336","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000040","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent Internet Protocol (IP) source routing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> MSS: (DisableIPSourceRouting) IP source routing protection level (protects against packet spoofing) to \"Enabled\" with \"Highest protection, source routing is completely disabled\" selected.\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisableIPSourceRouting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to disable IP source routing protects against spoofing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6419","uuid":"e44f526b-82f2-443a-aaf8-b9d196eb8c87","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A07EEFA7C017760081AB2AF856245C0D59417A8F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 source routing must be configured to the highest protection level to prevent Internet Protocol (IP) source routing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254337","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254337","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254337","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254337r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254337","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000050","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF)-generated routes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> MSS: (EnableICMPRedirect) Allow ICMP redirects to override OSPF generated routes to \"Disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Tcpip\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableICMPRedirect\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing ICMP redirect of routes can lead to traffic not being routed properly. When disabled, this forces ICMP to be routed via the shortest path first.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5405","uuid":"d5db526c-81a2-46a7-9e86-f19982ee98f6","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AE591E2A168318A4657192837A40F201A999BED2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to prevent Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) redirects from overriding Open Shortest Path First (OSPF)-generated routes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254338","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254338","title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254338","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000420-GPOS-00186","rule_id_src":"SV-254338r958902_rule","rule_id":"SV-254338","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000060","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MSS (Legacy) >> MSS: (NoNameReleaseOnDemand) Allow the computer to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the MSS-Legacy custom templates included with the STIG package. \"MSS-Legacy.admx\" and \"MSS-Legacy.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netbt\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name:  NoNameReleaseOnDemand\n\nValue Type:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Configuring the system to ignore name release requests, except from WINS servers, prevents a denial of service (DoS) attack. The DoS consists of sending a NetBIOS name release request to the server for each entry in the server's cache, causing a response delay in the normal operation of the server's WINS resolution capability.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002385"],"reference_identifier":"9038","uuid":"030a2dd0-5a9f-434c-a027-b6854061e6a6","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5FA5D5284057AC76A5A9403221EE179D49C19F92\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to ignore NetBIOS name release requests except from WINS servers.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254339","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254339","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254339","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254339r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254339","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000070","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 insecure logons to an SMB server must be disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Lanman Workstation >> Enable insecure guest logons to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\LanmanWorkstation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowInsecureGuestAuth\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Insecure guest logons allow unauthenticated access to shared folders. Shared resources on a system must require authentication to establish proper access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8274","uuid":"b83e36f2-d4f8-46a9-b98f-182b764068dc","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 168A7399436D460CEC8BF8780E1E8CBB49306899\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 insecure logons to an SMB server must be disabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254340","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254340","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254340","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254340r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254340","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000080","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 hardened Universal Naming Convention (UNC) paths must be defined to require mutual authentication and integrity for at least the \\\\*\\SYSVOL and \\\\*\\NETLOGON shares.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Network >> Network Provider >> Hardened UNC Paths\" to \"Enabled\" with at least the following configured in \"Hardened UNC Paths\" (click the \"Show\" button to display):\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain-joined systems. For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry values do not exist or are not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\NetworkProvider\\HardenedPaths\\\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\NETLOGON\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nValue Name: \\\\*\\SYSVOL\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: RequireMutualAuthentication=1, RequireIntegrity=1\n\nAdditional entries would not be a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Additional security requirements are applied to UNC paths specified in hardened UNC paths before allowing access to them. This aids in preventing tampering with or spoofing of connections to these paths.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4246","uuid":"ed7fec69-fee1-41da-9852-ee24eb0236b9","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B5FF67BA99CAAAE65019D93BF2290C92BCF1A494\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 hardened Universal Naming Convention (UNC) paths must be defined to require mutual authentication and integrity for at least the \\\\*\\SYSVOL and \\\\*\\NETLOGON shares.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254341","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254341","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254341","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","rule_id_src":"SV-254341r958422_rule","rule_id":"SV-254341","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000090","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 command line data must be included in process creation events.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Audit Process Creation >> Include command line in process creation events to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\Audit\\\n\nValue Name: ProcessCreationIncludeCmdLine_Enabled\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling \"Include command line data for process creation events\" will record the command line information with the process creation events in the log. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000135"],"reference_identifier":"4836","uuid":"5d2c7f6a-3790-4dcf-85fd-e6bc15f57ef9","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A9ADB68B679A5A34579DFBB864CA6EFD963DD0F2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 command line data must be included in process creation events.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254342","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254342","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254342","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254342r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254342","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000100","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to enable Remote host allows delegation of nonexportable credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Credentials Delegation >> Remote host allows delegation of nonexportable credentials to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CredentialsDelegation\\\n\nValue Name: AllowProtectedCreds\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An exportable version of credentials is provided to remote hosts when using credential delegation which exposes them to theft on the remote host. Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard allow delegation of nonexportable credentials providing additional protection of the credentials. Enabling this configures the host to support Restricted Admin mode or Remote Credential Guard.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"5473","uuid":"86c2b9d8-2931-4cfb-b601-424b5b4509b3","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7C709C004D963BDF1147C1EEDCF28D4B59C60888\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to enable Remote host allows delegation of nonexportable credentials.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254343","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254343","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254343","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254343r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254343","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000110","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 virtualization-based security must be enabled with the platform security level configured to Secure Boot or Secure Boot with DMA Protection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Guard >> Turn On Virtualization Based Security to \"Enabled\" with \"Secure Boot\" or \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" selected.\n\nA Microsoft TechNet article on Credential Guard, including system requirement details, can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard","weight":"10.0","check_content":"For standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\n\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"RequiredSecurityProperties\" does not include a value of \"2\" indicating \"Secure Boot\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"3\" will also be displayed in the results (e.g., \"{1, 2, 3}\").\n\nIf \"VirtualizationBasedSecurityStatus\" is not a value of \"2\" indicating \"Running\", this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\n\nIf \"Device Guard Virtualization based security\" does not display \"Running\", this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Device Guard Required Security Properties\" does not display \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot\", this is a finding.\n\nIf \"Secure Boot and DMA Protection\" is configured, \"DMA Protection\" will also be displayed (e.g., \"Base Virtualization Support, Secure Boot, DMA Protection\").\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry values; however, due to hardware requirements, the registry values alone do not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: EnableVirtualizationBasedSecurity\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nValue Name: RequirePlatformSecurityFeatures\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Secure Boot only) or 0x00000003 (3) (Secure Boot and DMA Protection)\n\nA Microsoft TechNet article on Credential Guard, including system requirement details, can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://technet.microsoft.com/itpro/windows/keep-secure/credential-guard","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Virtualization Based Security (VBS) provides the platform for the additional security features Credential Guard and virtualization-based protection of code integrity. Secure Boot is the minimum security level, with DMA protection providing additional memory protection. DMA Protection requires a CPU that supports input/output memory management unit (IOMMU).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7777","uuid":"5f5f866d-dc6d-45c5-b9a0-ae8dd1a78103","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E24A24E1A794B0F83FC1E5599A9CDADF84E134F8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 virtualization-based security must be enabled with the platform security level configured to Secure Boot or Secure Boot with DMA Protection.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254344","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254344","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254344","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254344r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254344","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000130","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must prevent boot drivers identified as bad.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nIf this needs to be corrected or a more secure setting is desired, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Early Launch Antimalware >> Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy to \"Not Configured\" or \"Enabled\" with any option other than \"All\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Early Launch Antimalware - Boot-Start Driver Initialization policy to enforce \"Good, unknown and bad but critical\" (preventing \"bad\").\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0x00000007 (7)\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Policies\\EarlyLaunch\\\n\nValue Name: DriverLoadPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1), 0x00000003 (3), or 0x00000008 (8) (or if the Value Name does not exist)\n\nPossible values for this setting are:\n8 - Good only\n1 - Good and unknown\n3 - Good, unknown and bad but critical\n7 - All (which includes \"bad\" and would be a finding)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Compromised boot drivers can introduce malware prior to protection mechanisms that load after initialization. The Early Launch Antimalware driver can limit allowed drivers based on classifications determined by the malware protection application. At a minimum, drivers determined to be bad must not be allowed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6798","uuid":"af17d64c-cbad-46b8-8361-4b1ec964c63a","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FF009BB4CE0C51068FD94BC7B7F35ACEC85946FD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Early Launch Antimalware, Boot-Start Driver Initialization Policy must prevent boot drivers identified as bad.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254345","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254345","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254345","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254345r1135378_rule","rule_id":"SV-254345","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000140","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 group policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Group Policy >> Configure registry policy processing to \"Enabled\" with the option \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is not applicable for Domain Controllers.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Group Policy\\{35378EAC-683F-11D2-A89A-00C04FBBCFA2}\\\n\nValue Name: NoGPOListChanges\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Registry entries for group policy settings can potentially be changed from the required configuration. This could occur as part of troubleshooting or by a malicious process on a compromised system. Enabling this setting and then selecting the \"Process even if the Group Policy objects have not changed\" option ensures the policies will be reprocessed even if none have been changed. This way, any unauthorized changes are forced to match the domain-based group policy settings again.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2512","uuid":"7c30822a-7cb3-4cd0-ac9d-7f08ab766660","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 53CB906D889B8B06D417FF8092133958D9867577\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 group policy objects must be reprocessed even if they have not changed.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254346","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254346","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254346","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254346r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254346","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000150","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> Turn off downloading of print drivers over HTTP to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableWebPnPDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and will prevent uncontrolled updates to the system. \n\nThis setting prevents the computer from downloading print driver packages over HTTP.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"4323","uuid":"b7fdc2b5-246e-4eb6-8592-6fa1607ade81","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E3F62AC264D0345F7B995FA708BB83B8DDC95373\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 downloading print driver packages over HTTP must be turned off.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254347","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254347","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254347","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254347r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254347","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000160","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 printing over HTTP must be turned off.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Internet Communication Management >> Internet Communication settings >> Turn off printing over HTTP to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Printers\\\n\nValue Name: DisableHTTPPrinting\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and will prevent uncontrolled updates to the system.\n\nThis setting prevents the client computer from printing over HTTP, which allows the computer to print to printers on the intranet as well as the internet.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6607","uuid":"1934cc91-4dce-49ab-947b-39b3ff1ca117","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6FB664CE764507548632836A4004714BF866131E\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 printing over HTTP must be turned off.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254348","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254348","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254348","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254348r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254348","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000170","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 network selection user interface (UI) must not be displayed on the logon screen.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Logon >> Do not display network selection UI to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the registry value below. If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DontDisplayNetworkSelectionUI\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling interaction with the network selection UI allows users to change connections to available networks without signing in to Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3884","uuid":"d53b8600-284a-439b-805f-c9cd57548f7e","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254349","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254349","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254349","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254349r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254349","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000180","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (on battery).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Power Management >> Sleep Settings >> Require a password when a computer wakes (on battery) to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\\\n\nValue Name: DCSettingIndex\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system that does not require authentication when resuming from sleep may provide access to unauthorized users. Authentication must always be required when accessing a system. This setting ensures users are prompted for a password when the system wakes from sleep (on battery).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9469","uuid":"e05a30d7-7c5a-421a-bdd2-f2dc3bfaa32d","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254350","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254350","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254350","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254350r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254350","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000190","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (plugged in).","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Power Management >> Sleep Settings >> Require a password when a computer wakes (plugged in) to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Power\\PowerSettings\\0e796bdb-100d-47d6-a2d5-f7d2daa51f51\\\n\nValue Name: ACSettingIndex\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system that does not require authentication when resuming from sleep may provide access to unauthorized users. Authentication must always be required when accessing a system. This setting ensures users are prompted for a password when the system wakes from sleep (plugged in).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4267","uuid":"515b4900-cc7a-4d22-bb59-2e3d8faefc0c","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DDBB883DEDC324FC68689F37BFF0E439525F11E8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 users must be prompted to authenticate when the system wakes from sleep (plugged in).' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254351","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254351","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254351","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254351r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254351","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000200","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Application Compatibility Program Inventory must be prevented from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Application Compatibility >> Turn off Inventory Collector to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\AppCompat\\\n\nValue Name: DisableInventory\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Turning off this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise and will prevent uncontrolled updates to the system.\n\nThis setting will prevent the Program Inventory from collecting data about a system and sending the information to Microsoft.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"5429","uuid":"9f017f15-d2a1-48c5-bf6b-44353bf4f389","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 97F66542B9E277634F9C5B3F38DE7BD6E75B3DAF\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 Application Compatibility Program Inventory must be prevented from collecting data and sending the information to Microsoft.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254352","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254352","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254352","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-254352r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-254352","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000210","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Autoplay must be turned off for nonvolume devices.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> Disallow Autoplay for nonvolume devices to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoAutoplayfornonVolume\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing AutoPlay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. AutoPlay begins reading from a drive as soon as media is inserted into the drive. As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start. This setting will disable AutoPlay for nonvolume devices, such as Media Transfer Protocol (MTP) devices.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"6233","uuid":"8222c960-04d2-4f32-a99f-fcf071c36de8","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B097645AE1836804946273FE46B3D50307DD5925\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Autoplay must be turned off for nonvolume devices.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254353","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254353","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254353","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-254353r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-254353","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000220","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 default AutoRun behavior must be configured to prevent AutoRun commands.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> Set the default behavior for AutoRun to \"Enabled\" with \"Do not execute any autorun commands\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoAutorun\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing AutoRun commands to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. Configuring this setting prevents AutoRun commands from executing.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"4978","uuid":"33497133-db3c-45aa-9992-a01d5663fa13","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6C2E3541FF84BA33FE76DEC7D561C6FC05F988FE\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 default AutoRun behavior must be configured to prevent AutoRun commands.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254354","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254354","title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254354","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000368-GPOS-00154","rule_id_src":"SV-254354r958804_rule","rule_id":"SV-254354","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000230","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 AutoPlay must be disabled for all drives.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> AutoPlay Policies >> Turn off AutoPlay to \"Enabled\" with \"All Drives\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDriveTypeAutoRun\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x000000ff (255)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing AutoPlay to execute may introduce malicious code to a system. AutoPlay begins reading from a drive as soon media is inserted into the drive. As a result, the setup file of programs or music on audio media may start. By default, AutoPlay is disabled on removable drives, such as the floppy disk drive (but not the CD-ROM drive) and on network drives. Enabling this policy disables AutoPlay on all drives.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001764"],"reference_identifier":"9181","uuid":"717f8703-4828-4a6d-a414-5a5aea010aa1","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B6762BF75A9D9B7489DDDE52325703A32A0F22FF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 AutoPlay must be disabled for all drives.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254355","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254355","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254355","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-254355r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-254355","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000240","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 administrator accounts must not be enumerated during elevation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Credential User Interface >> Enumerate administrator accounts on elevation to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\CredUI\\\n\nValue Name: EnumerateAdministrators\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enumeration of administrator accounts when elevating can provide part of the logon information to an unauthorized user. This setting configures the system to always require users to type in a username and password to elevate a running application.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"7174","uuid":"7e1df7bc-fa23-4c45-9cae-273f1a62480e","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254356","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254356","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254356","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254356r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254356","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000250","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Diagnostic Data must be configured to send \"required diagnostic data\" or \"optional diagnostic data\".","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Data Collection and Preview Build >> Allow Diagnostic Data to \"Enabled\" with \"Send required diagnostic data\" selected or \"Send optional diagnostic data\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DataCollection\\\n\nValue Name: AllowTelemetry\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1), 0x00000003 (3)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Some features may communicate with the vendor, sending system information or downloading data or components for the feature. Limiting this capability will prevent potentially sensitive information from being sent outside the enterprise. The \"send required diagnostic data\" option for Allow Diagnostic Data configures the lowest amount of data, effectively none outside of the Malicious Software Removal Tool (MSRT), Defender, and Diagnostic Data client settings. \"Optional Diagnostic Data\" sends basic diagnostic and usage data and may be required to support some Microsoft services.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"4001","uuid":"a1c5063b-a976-4cc5-9788-31d12f3cd5e0","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 402FD002E012F808023C82FF35DD4FE520ADA4AC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Diagnostic Data must be configured to send \"required diagnostic data\" or \"optional diagnostic data\".' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254357","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254357","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254357","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254357r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254357","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000260","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the internet.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Delivery Optimization >> Download Mode to \"Enabled\" with any option except \"Internet\" selected.\n\nAcceptable selections include:\n\nHTTP only (0)\nLAN (1)\nGroup (2)\nInternet (3)\nSimple (99)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeliveryOptimization\\\n\nValue Name: DODownloadMode\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) - No peering (HTTP Only)\n0x00000001 (1) - Peers on same NAT only (LAN)\n0x00000002 (2) - Local Network / Private group peering (Group)\n0x00000063 (99) - Simple download mode, no peering (Simple)\n\nA value of 0x00000003 (3), Internet, is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows Update can obtain updates from additional sources instead of Microsoft. In addition to Microsoft, updates can be obtained from and sent to PCs on the local network as well as on the internet. This is part of the Windows Update trusted process; however, to minimize outside exposure, obtaining updates from or sending to systems on the internet must be prevented.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6324","uuid":"b3ed84a5-5730-4a1e-ab96-440b79656dbb","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 38AEBCA63EF9A3A4DC66243116EA5BC08A15A88A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Windows Update must not obtain updates from other PCs on the internet.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254358","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254358","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254358","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-254358r958752_rule","rule_id":"SV-254358","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000270","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Application event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> Application >> Specify the maximum log file size (KB) to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to write events directly to an audit server, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Application\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"8918","uuid":"0afef3e9-35d3-47f7-ab0a-0fe7959f8fcb","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254359","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254359","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254359","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-254359r1186393_rule","rule_id":"SV-254359","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000280","rule_title":"The Windows Server 2022 security event log size must be configured to a value that holds at least one week's worth of audit records.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> Security >> Specify the maximum log file size (KB) to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of a value that will contain one week of audit records or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to write events directly to an audit server, this is not applicable.\n\nThe registry configuration setting below must be set (at least) to a value equal to the size needed to contain one week's worth of audit records in the security event log. The value used below is an example that assumes a typical week\u2019s log size of 5GB.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nNote: The following registry entry is an example; the value must equal at least one week's worth of records.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\Security\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue:0x49960800 (5120000) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel. System administrators (SAs) must monitor the volume of security event audit records and increase the registry value for the log size as needed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"4086","uuid":"a40e121a-ecfd-4fde-bb36-d03fed3f2932","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AF2E65768D3A06CBCFC1C4A506D2D86EE77B176B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The Windows Server 2022 security event log size must be configured to a value that holds at least one week's worth of audit records.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254360","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254360","title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254360","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000341-GPOS-00132","rule_id_src":"SV-254360r958752_rule","rule_id":"SV-254360","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000290","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Event Log Service >> System >> Specify the maximum log file size (KB) to \"Enabled\" with a \"Maximum Log Size (KB)\" of \"32768\" or greater.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the system is configured to write events directly to an audit server, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\EventLog\\System\\\n\nValue Name: MaxSize\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00008000 (32768) (or greater)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inadequate log size will cause the log to fill up quickly. This may prevent audit events from being recorded properly and require frequent attention by administrative personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001849"],"reference_identifier":"6024","uuid":"321d8959-65f9-4a56-8e36-c14c92c5cec2","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6BED0F3221A289E1C9C71CCE76474A4C0C4D9ACB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 System event log size must be configured to 32768 KB or greater.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254361","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254361","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254361","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254361r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254361","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000300","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Microsoft Defender antivirus SmartScreen must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> Configure Windows Defender SmartScreen to \"Enabled\" with either option \"Warn\" or \"Warn and prevent bypass\" selected.\n\nWindows Server 2022 includes duplicate policies for this setting. It can also be configured under Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Defender SmartScreen >> Explorer.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems; for other systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSmartScreen\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Microsoft Defender antivirus SmartScreen helps protect systems from programs downloaded from the internet that may be malicious. Enabling SmartScreen can block potentially malicious programs or warn users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"9392","uuid":"4d608667-7465-4cc9-bb6b-44c42e847783","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C2CECB33EC93E95D2B5ABCD5187B7C2CCB4450EF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Microsoft Defender antivirus SmartScreen must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254362","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254362","title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254362","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","rule_id_src":"SV-254362r958928_rule","rule_id":"SV-254362","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000310","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for data execution prevention to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> Turn off Data Execution Prevention for Explorer to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Data Execution Prevention to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoDataExecutionPrevention\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Data Execution Prevention provides additional protection by performing checks on memory to help prevent malicious code from running. This setting will prevent Data Execution Prevention from being turned off for File Explorer.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002824"],"reference_identifier":"2528","uuid":"39111e97-3cc5-451c-bb67-3f46448781f8","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8998C7E4236750DCA7E377EEEDD72AE1E79D6121\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Explorer Data Execution Prevention must be enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254363","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254363","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254363","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254363r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254363","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000320","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Turning off File Explorer heap termination on corruption must be disabled.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be disabled.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> Turn off heap termination on corruption to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for File Explorer heap termination on corruption to be enabled.\n\nIf the registry Value Name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: NoHeapTerminationOnCorruption\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Legacy plug-in applications may continue to function when a File Explorer session has become corrupt. Disabling this feature will prevent this.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6416","uuid":"e65ac2af-7652-41c6-ab2e-1787bc6ed336","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254364","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254364","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254364","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254364r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254364","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000330","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 File Explorer shell protocol must run in protected mode.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> File Explorer >> Turn off shell protocol protected mode to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for shell protected mode to be turned on for File Explorer.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Explorer\\\n\nValue Name: PreXPSP2ShellProtocolBehavior\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The shell protocol will limit the set of folders that applications can open when run in protected mode. Restricting files an application can open to a limited set of folders increases the security of Windows.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7995","uuid":"8973c75b-400f-419f-b6c4-2c48a3b70b41","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254365","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254365","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254365","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-254365r1051096_rule","rule_id":"SV-254365","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000340","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must not save passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Connection Client >> Do not allow passwords to be saved to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordSaving\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client could allow an unauthorized user to establish a remote desktop session to another system. The system must be configured to prevent users from saving passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"3266","uuid":"36e0229a-b68a-449d-9384-de1119ad8585","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FCD2BB070A255BF65C8D278A326FDCE06B5AE2F4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must not save passwords in the Remote Desktop Client.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254366","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254366","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254366","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-254366r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-254366","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000350","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must prevent drive redirection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Device and Resource Redirection >> Do not allow drive redirection to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fDisableCdm\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Preventing users from sharing the local drives on their client computers with Remote Session Hosts that they access helps reduce possible exposure of sensitive data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"7658","uuid":"9245d8f3-8657-465f-ad58-40944ce1c0b3","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DDC6F72BC76795E09DCD5F080EAADF2CF383FCEF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must prevent drive redirection.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254367","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254367","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254367","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-254367r1051097_rule","rule_id":"SV-254367","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000360","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> Always prompt for password upon connection to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fPromptForPassword\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting controls the ability of users to supply passwords automatically as part of their remote desktop connection. Disabling this setting would allow anyone to use the stored credentials in a connection item to connect to the terminal server.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"7612","uuid":"a67acf7e-b99e-4e7d-94c3-57e448bdf648","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8AABC313D36173DB2AAED7923896D10792371D13\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must always prompt a client for passwords upon connection.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254368","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254368","title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254368","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","rule_id_src":"SV-254368r958408_rule","rule_id":"SV-254368","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000370","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must require secure Remote Procedure Call (RPC) communications.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> Require secure RPC communication to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: fEncryptRPCTraffic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Allowing unsecure RPC communication exposes the system to man-in-the-middle attacks and data disclosure attacks. A man-in-the-middle attack occurs when an intruder captures packets between a client and server and modifies them before allowing the packets to be exchanged. Usually the attacker will modify the information in the packets in an attempt to cause either the client or server to reveal sensitive information.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014, SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000068","CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"2588","uuid":"3523b121-e2d9-4698-8b2a-ae0ccd8c7afb","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EF667A0A886E3F45AE95509F64FF3BBD1D6944B7\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must require secure Remote Procedure Call (RPC) communications.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254369","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254369","title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254369","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014","rule_id_src":"SV-254369r958408_rule","rule_id":"SV-254369","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000380","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to High Level.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Remote Desktop Services >> Remote Desktop Session Host >> Security >> Set client connection encryption level to \"Enabled\" with \"High Level\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Terminal Services\\\n\nValue Name: MinEncryptionLevel\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000003 (3)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Remote connections must be encrypted to prevent interception of data or sensitive information. Selecting \"High Level\" will ensure encryption of Remote Desktop Services sessions in both directions.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000033-GPOS-00014, SRG-OS-000250-GPOS-00093","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000068","CCI-001453"],"reference_identifier":"1574","uuid":"5dfec599-0b96-4daa-9696-ab9e354ab3b4","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2F3C6858923E117E23EDAD5DAC05FB9D5BF86145\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Remote Desktop Services must be configured with the client connection encryption set to High Level.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254370","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254370","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254370","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254370r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254370","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000390","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> RSS Feeds >> Prevent downloading of enclosures to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: DisableEnclosureDownload\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Attachments from RSS feeds may not be secure. This setting will prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9504","uuid":"364d94b8-a92c-4d50-bcd9-b4d28ce3f773","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AB64A867A06D6F393B574F44951908C54D643A70\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must prevent attachments from being downloaded from RSS feeds.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254371","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254371","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254371","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254371r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254371","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000400","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must disable Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> RSS Feeds >> Turn on Basic feed authentication over HTTP to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for the Windows RSS platform to not use Basic authentication over HTTP connections.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Feeds\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasicAuthInClear\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain-text passwords that could be used to compromise a system. Disabling Basic authentication will reduce this potential.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"1564","uuid":"2ed43a99-6529-47d1-8449-71984cd11f4e","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D56C822D634424467F96121C4E64449AC44BABC4\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must disable Basic authentication for RSS feeds over HTTP.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254372","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254372","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254372","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254372r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254372","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000410","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent Indexing of encrypted files.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Search >> Allow indexing of encrypted files to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Windows Search\\\n\nValue Name: AllowIndexingEncryptedStoresOrItems\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Indexing of encrypted files may expose sensitive data. This setting prevents encrypted files from being indexed.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"3863","uuid":"b9be78a1-440d-4edd-be97-26e8bd2446f0","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 499463E3C3D72E4A0E25872B3794118100A43205\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must prevent Indexing of encrypted files.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254373","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254373","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254373","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-254373r1051098_rule","rule_id":"SV-254373","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000420","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent users from changing installation options.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> Allow user control over installs to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: EnableUserControl\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Installation options for applications are typically controlled by administrators. This setting prevents users from changing installation options that may bypass security features.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"5591","uuid":"2747b348-bef0-4ff7-9b41-e685404bd72e","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D7ED84BE998B6D7B20E468A8B09141B4802AD132\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must prevent users from changing installation options.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254374","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254374","title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254374","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000362-GPOS-00149","rule_id_src":"SV-254374r1051099_rule","rule_id":"SV-254374","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000430","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must disable the Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges option.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> Always install with elevated privileges to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: AlwaysInstallElevated\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Standard user accounts must not be granted elevated privileges. Enabling Windows Installer to elevate privileges when installing applications can allow malicious persons and applications to gain full control of a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-003980","CCI-001812"],"reference_identifier":"5847","uuid":"757d1902-696d-4f40-b692-3f8dcd6ec8d3","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: EEBC4E622411DF87F8B480581FFB036656F25879\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must disable the Windows Installer Always install with elevated privileges option.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254375","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254375","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254375","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254375r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254375","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000440","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.","fix_text":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf this needs to be corrected, configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Installer >> Prevent Internet Explorer security prompt for Windows Installer scripts to \"Not Configured\" or \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The default behavior is for Internet Explorer to warn users and select whether to allow or refuse installation when a web-based program attempts to install software on the system.\n\nIf the registry value name below does not exist, this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"0\", this is not a finding.\n\nIf it exists and is configured with a value of \"1\", this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Installer\\\n\nValue Name: SafeForScripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0) (or if the Value Name does not exist)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Web-based programs may attempt to install malicious software on a system. Ensuring users are notified if a web-based program attempts to install software allows them to refuse the installation.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3062","uuid":"e0bf7ed9-06b2-4be8-ad18-223375d646a7","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 784D325D66EF3191E4611E1FDBD7CE944002B97A\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 users must be notified if a web-based program attempts to install software.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254376","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254376","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254376","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00229","rule_id_src":"SV-254376r991591_rule","rule_id":"SV-254376","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000450","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must disable automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Logon Options >> Sign-in and lock last interactive user automatically after a restart to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the registry value below. If it does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: DisableAutomaticRestartSignOn\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Windows can be configured to automatically sign the user back in after a Windows Update restart. Some protections are in place to help ensure this is done in a secure fashion; however, disabling this will prevent the caching of credentials for this purpose and also ensure the user is aware of the restart.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"7928","uuid":"68878daf-b1bb-4fce-9127-fb48b908a8db","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FF6E7A2FE55E8ACF09E1F08B4385E3C110BBFFDB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must disable automatically signing in the last interactive user after a system-initiated restart.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254377","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254377","title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254377","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000042-GPOS-00020","rule_id_src":"SV-254377r958422_rule","rule_id":"SV-254377","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000460","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 PowerShell script block logging must be enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows PowerShell >> Turn on PowerShell Script Block Logging to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\ScriptBlockLogging\\\n\nValue Name: EnableScriptBlockLogging\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling PowerShell script block logging will record detailed information from the processing of PowerShell commands and scripts. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000135"],"reference_identifier":"1111","uuid":"9defa37f-a5a3-4cb8-bbfb-7bd33898166b","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 56AAE92B12127162A9FD8243F50467B6CBC7BE5B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 PowerShell script block logging must be enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254378","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254378","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254378","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","rule_id_src":"SV-254378r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-254378","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000470","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Basic authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> Allow Basic authentication to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain-text passwords that could be used to compromise a system. Disabling Basic authentication will reduce this potential.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"3080","uuid":"2eb861cc-10a6-4ada-aaf4-d77c26bf80f9","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F8FA30B909F705DA629890D0903E6861C2934B71\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Basic authentication.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254379","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254379","title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254379","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","rule_id_src":"SV-254379r958848_rule","rule_id":"SV-254379","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000480","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not allow unencrypted traffic.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> Allow unencrypted traffic to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowUnencryptedTraffic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unencrypted remote access to a system can allow sensitive information to be compromised. Windows remote management connections must be encrypted to prevent this.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173, SRG-OS-000394-GPOS-00174","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002890","CCI-003123"],"reference_identifier":"6343","uuid":"30dc2a29-571f-42ff-abbd-90e803f7cc05","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 45AFF1E214057322D5F82DB7663DA30F9C855074\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not allow unencrypted traffic.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254380","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254380","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254380","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","rule_id_src":"SV-254380r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-254380","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000490","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Digest authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Client >> Disallow Digest authentication to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Client\\\n\nValue Name: AllowDigest\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Digest authentication is not as strong as other options and may be subject to man-in-the-middle attacks. Disallowing Digest authentication will reduce this potential.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"4720","uuid":"837d750c-dabd-47f8-812f-ab87b4ca4f0f","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D377D9289CA98E31B83AFE2861C0FD4ACFADD840\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) client must not use Digest authentication.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254381","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254381","title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254381","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000125-GPOS-00065","rule_id_src":"SV-254381r958510_rule","rule_id":"SV-254381","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000500","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not use Basic authentication.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> Allow Basic authentication to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBasic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Basic authentication uses plain-text passwords that could be used to compromise a system. Disabling Basic authentication will reduce this potential.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000877"],"reference_identifier":"9514","uuid":"96e844c1-39a1-4035-8e2a-738142044e69","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6411B519A03675C4E31F8DEA70FF4FBEA7F2B4C2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not use Basic authentication.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254382","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254382","title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254382","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173","rule_id_src":"SV-254382r958848_rule","rule_id":"SV-254382","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000510","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not allow unencrypted traffic.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> Allow unencrypted traffic to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: AllowUnencryptedTraffic\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unencrypted remote access to a system can allow sensitive information to be compromised. Windows remote management connections must be encrypted to prevent this.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000393-GPOS-00173, SRG-OS-000394-GPOS-00174","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002890","CCI-003123"],"reference_identifier":"6577","uuid":"d7935f5b-102d-4b8c-9af9-97d359dd685f","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 016599E0204AC9132B9EF3E886ECDDBC23FD76ED\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not allow unencrypted traffic.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254383","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254383","title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254383","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156","rule_id_src":"SV-254383r1051100_rule","rule_id":"SV-254383","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000520","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows Remote Management (WinRM) >> WinRM Service >> Disallow WinRM from storing RunAs credentials to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\WinRM\\Service\\\n\nValue Name: DisableRunAs\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Storage of administrative credentials could allow unauthorized access. Disallowing the storage of RunAs credentials for Windows Remote Management will prevent them from being used with plug-ins.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00156, SRG-OS-000373-GPOS-00157","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002038"],"reference_identifier":"1200","uuid":"ca38944d-88dc-44bb-97eb-808c99bc9344","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 208F5C56E1AE7DF4C94AE6F523089AEE66634E75\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service must not store RunAs credentials.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254384","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254384","title":"SRG-OS-000041-GPOS-00019","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254384","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000041-GPOS-00019","rule_id_src":"SV-254384r958420_rule","rule_id":"SV-254384","rule_version":"WN22-CC-000530","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have PowerShell Transcription enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> Windows Components >> Windows PowerShell >> \"Turn on PowerShell Transcription\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSpecify the Transcript output directory to point to a Central Log Server or another secure location to prevent user access.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\PowerShell\\Transcription\\\n\nValue Name: EnableTranscripting\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nEnabling PowerShell Transcription will record detailed information from the processing of PowerShell commands and scripts. This can provide additional detail when malware has run on a system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000134"],"reference_identifier":"4621","uuid":"aa4d9eba-a230-4af2-bec7-665d680602fb","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 873E466DE00A50C81679531891550F82BB73FF13\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must have PowerShell Transcription enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254385","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254385","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254385","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254385r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254385","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000010","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must only allow administrators responsible for the domain controller to have Administrator rights on the system.","fix_text":"Configure the Administrators group to include only administrator groups or accounts that are responsible for the system.\n\nRemove any standard user accounts.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nReview the Administrators group. Only the appropriate administrator groups or accounts responsible for administration of the system may be members of the group.\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the local administrator group.\n\nIf prohibited accounts are members of the local administrators group, this is a finding.\n\nIf the built-in Administrator account or other required administrative accounts are found on the system, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An account that does not have Administrator duties must not have Administrator rights. Such rights would allow the account to bypass or modify required security restrictions on that machine and make it vulnerable to attack.\n\nSystem administrators must log on to systems using only accounts with the minimum level of authority necessary. \n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the built-in Administrators group.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"5063","uuid":"5b6d929b-ffec-4b3a-9ba8-65e37be6c882","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 42FACA526D0BB2653182D90B9A0EA8DC91D4B9AC\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must only allow administrators responsible for the domain controller to have Administrator rights on the system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254386","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254386","title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254386","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","rule_id_src":"SV-254386r1051101_rule","rule_id":"SV-254386","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000020","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Kerberos user logon restrictions must be enforced.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value in the Default Domain Policy for Computer Configuration >> Policies >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Kerberos Policy >> Enforce user logon restrictions to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the following is configured in the Default Domain Policy:\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the Domain being reviewed (Forest >> Domains >> Domain). \n\nRight-click on the \"Default Domain Policy\".\n\nSelect \"Edit\".\n\nNavigate to Computer Configuration >> Policies >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Kerberos Policy.\n\nIf the \"Enforce user logon restrictions\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the Kerberos Key Distribution Center (KDC) validates every request for a session ticket against the user rights policy of the target computer. The policy is enabled by default, which is the most secure setting for validating that access to target resources is not circumvented.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057, SRG-OS-000113-GPOS-00058","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"reference_identifier":"3170","uuid":"0229087b-4dc9-4257-8b6b-35dcf26142bf","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E461C0A1481CDBBFF43DD18235917EF3862CA975\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Kerberos user logon restrictions must be enforced.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254387","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254387","title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254387","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","rule_id_src":"SV-254387r1051102_rule","rule_id":"SV-254387","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000030","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Kerberos service ticket maximum lifetime must be limited to 600 minutes or less.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value in the Default Domain Policy for Computer Configuration >> Policies >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Kerberos Policy >> Maximum lifetime for service ticket to a maximum of \"600\" minutes, but not \"0\", which equates to \"Ticket doesn't expire\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the following is configured in the Default Domain Policy:\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the Domain being reviewed (Forest >> Domains >> Domain). \n\nRight-click on the \"Default Domain Policy\".\n\nSelect \"Edit\".\n\nNavigate to Computer Configuration >> Policies >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Kerberos Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Maximum lifetime for service ticket\" is \"0\" or greater than \"600\" minutes, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting determines the maximum amount of time (in minutes) that a granted session ticket can be used to access a particular service. Session tickets are used only to authenticate new connections with servers. Ongoing operations are not interrupted if the session ticket used to authenticate the connection expires during the connection.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057, SRG-OS-000113-GPOS-00058","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"reference_identifier":"8795","uuid":"6867cb3e-7803-484b-ad8b-42dbb7aa909c","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4C5396DBA2157EC371947A82E85B38047940C660\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Kerberos service ticket maximum lifetime must be limited to 600 minutes or less.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254388","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254388","title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254388","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","rule_id_src":"SV-254388r1051103_rule","rule_id":"SV-254388","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000040","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Kerberos user ticket lifetime must be limited to 10 hours or less.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value in the Default Domain Policy for Computer Configuration >> Policies >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Kerberos Policy >> Maximum lifetime for user ticket to a maximum of \"10\" hours but not \"0\", which equates to \"Ticket doesn't expire\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the following is configured in the Default Domain Policy:\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the Domain being reviewed (Forest >> Domains >> Domain).\n\nRight-click on the \"Default Domain Policy\".\n\nSelect \"Edit\".\n\nNavigate to Computer Configuration >> Policies >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Kerberos Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Maximum lifetime for user ticket\" is \"0\" or greater than \"10\" hours, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"In Kerberos, there are two types of tickets: Ticket Granting Tickets (TGTs) and Service Tickets. Kerberos tickets have a limited lifetime so the time an attacker has to implement an attack is limited. This policy controls how long TGTs can be renewed. With Kerberos, the user's initial authentication to the domain controller results in a TGT, which is then used to request Service Tickets to resources. Upon startup, each computer gets a TGT before requesting a service ticket to the domain controller and any other computers it needs to access. For services that start up under a specified user account, users must always get a TGT first and then get Service Tickets to all computers and services accessed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057, SRG-OS-000113-GPOS-00058","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"reference_identifier":"3651","uuid":"f4f67a4a-0f35-4fca-a3b6-c8ca2e09072c","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4353718D725CB9CF171F52886BF974299FBE9BD8\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Kerberos user ticket lifetime must be limited to 10 hours or less.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254389","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254389","title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254389","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","rule_id_src":"SV-254389r1051104_rule","rule_id":"SV-254389","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000050","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Kerberos policy user ticket renewal maximum lifetime must be limited to seven days or less.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value in the Default Domain Policy for Computer Configuration >> Policies >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Kerberos Policy >> Maximum lifetime for user ticket renewal to a maximum of \"7\" days or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the following is configured in the Default Domain Policy:\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the Domain being reviewed (Forest >> Domains >> Domain).\n \nRight-click on the \"Default Domain Policy\".\n\nSelect \"Edit\".\n\nNavigate to Computer Configuration >> Policies >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Kerberos Policy.\n\nIf the \"Maximum lifetime for user ticket renewal\" is greater than \"7\" days, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting determines the period of time (in days) during which a user's Ticket Granting Ticket (TGT) may be renewed. This security configuration limits the amount of time an attacker has to crack the TGT and gain access.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057, SRG-OS-000113-GPOS-00058","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"reference_identifier":"7159","uuid":"7894ecc3-73be-420f-b60e-3ca5d416bf93","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DDBBB81EC60C723EBC59A957707FE0859E855B94\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Kerberos policy user ticket renewal maximum lifetime must be limited to seven days or less.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254390","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254390","title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254390","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057","rule_id_src":"SV-254390r1051105_rule","rule_id":"SV-254390","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000060","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 computer clock synchronization tolerance must be limited to five minutes or less.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value in the Default Domain Policy for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Kerberos Policy >> Maximum tolerance for computer clock synchronization to a maximum of \"5\" minutes or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the following is configured in the Default Domain Policy:\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the Domain being reviewed (Forest >> Domains >> Domain).\n \nRight-click on the \"Default Domain Policy\".\n\nSelect \"Edit\".\n\nNavigate to Computer Configuration >> Policies >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Account Policies >> Kerberos Policy.\n\nIf the \"Maximum tolerance for computer clock synchronization\" is greater than \"5\" minutes, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"This setting determines the maximum time difference (in minutes) that Kerberos will tolerate between the time on a client's clock and the time on a server's clock while still considering the two clocks synchronous. To prevent replay attacks, Kerberos uses timestamps as part of its protocol definition. For timestamps to work properly, the clocks of the client and the server need to be in sync as much as possible.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000112-GPOS-00057, SRG-OS-000113-GPOS-00058","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001941","CCI-001942"],"reference_identifier":"8804","uuid":"5e8d8dff-e41f-475b-8760-e074cd2cab5b","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 35BE22408AC0C8E6300604108CF32CE43A01ECE3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 computer clock synchronization tolerance must be limited to five minutes or less.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254391","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254391","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254391","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254391r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254391","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000070","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 permissions on the Active Directory data files must only allow System and Administrators access.","fix_text":"Maintain the permissions on NTDS database and log files as follows:\n\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(I)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(I)(F)\n\n(I) - permission inherited from parent container\n(F) - full access","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nRun \"Regedit\".\n\nNavigate to \"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\NTDS\\Parameters\".\n\nNote the directory locations in the values for:\n\nDatabase log files path\nDSA Database file\n\nBy default, they will be \\Windows\\NTDS.\n\nIf the locations are different, the following will need to be run for each.\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt (Admin)\".\n\nNavigate to the NTDS directory (\\Windows\\NTDS by default).\n\nRun \"icacls *.*\".\n\nIf the permissions on each file are not as restrictive as the following, this is a finding:\n\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(I)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(I)(F)\n\n(I) - permission inherited from parent container\n(F) - full access","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Improper access permissions for directory data-related files could allow unauthorized users to read, modify, or delete directory data or audit trails.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125, SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001314","CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"6912","uuid":"a76cd2e5-9f19-407d-acdc-642120dceac5","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254392","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254392","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254392","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254392r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254392","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000080","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory SYSVOL directory must have the proper access control permissions.","fix_text":"Maintain the permissions on the SYSVOL directory. Do not allow greater than \"Read & execute\" permissions for standard user accounts or groups. The defaults below meet this requirement:\n\nC:\\Windows\\SYSVOL\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\n\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read & execute - This folder, subfolder, and files\nServer Operators - Read & execute- This folder, subfolder, and files\nAdministrators - Special - This folder only (Special = Basic Permissions: all selected except Full control)\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nSYSTEM - Full control - This folder, subfolders, and files","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nOpen a command prompt.\n\nRun \"net share\".\n\nMake note of the directory location of the SYSVOL share.\n\nBy default, this will be \\Windows\\SYSVOL\\sysvol. For this requirement, permissions will be verified at the first SYSVOL directory level.\n\nIf any standard user accounts or groups have greater than \"Read & execute\" permissions, this is a finding. \n\nThe default permissions noted below meet this requirement:\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt\".\n\nRun \"icacls c:\\Windows\\SYSVOL\".\n\nThe following results must be displayed:\n\nNT AUTHORITY\\Authenticated Users:(RX)\nNT AUTHORITY\\Authenticated Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nBUILTIN\\Server Operators:(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Server Operators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(M,WDAC,WO)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\n\n(RX) - Read & execute \n\nRun \"icacls /help\" to view definitions of other permission codes.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Improper access permissions for directory data files could allow unauthorized users to read, modify, or delete directory data.\n\nThe SYSVOL directory contains public files (to the domain) such as policies and logon scripts. Data in shared subdirectories are replicated to all domain controllers in a domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2833","uuid":"78803156-2783-4309-8238-34d24fab5d16","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7574AC8FC3CEFB8A78059FAA285CCFDF2C6DD1FA\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Active Directory SYSVOL directory must have the proper access control permissions.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254393","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254393","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254393","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254393r1081073_rule","rule_id":"SV-254393","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000090","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Group Policy objects must have proper access control permissions.","fix_text":"Maintain the permissions on Group Policy objects to not allow greater than \"Read\" and \"Apply group policy\" for standard user accounts or groups. The default permissions below meet this requirement:\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Apply group policy, Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Authenticated Users are for Read-type Properties.\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\nSYSTEM - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nDomain Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nEnterprise Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions\n\nDocument any other access permissions that allow the objects to be updated with the ISSO.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the permissions on Group Policy objects.\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\" (available from various menus or run \"gpmc.msc\").\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the domain being reviewed (Forest >> Domains >> Domain).\n\nFor each Group Policy object:\n\nSelect the Group Policy object item in the left pane.\n\nSelect the \"Delegation\" tab in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\".\n\nSelect each Group or user name.\n\nView the permissions.\n\nIf any standard user accounts or groups have \"Allow\" permissions greater than \"Read\" and \"Apply group policy\", this is a finding.\n\nOther access permissions that allow the objects to be updated are considered findings unless specifically documented by the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe default permissions noted below satisfy this requirement. \n\nThe permissions shown are at the summary level. More detailed permissions can be viewed by selecting the next \"Advanced\" button, the desired Permission entry, and the \"Edit\" button.\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Apply group policy, Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Authenticated Users are for Read-type Properties. If detailed permissions include any Create, Delete, Modify, or Write Permissions or Properties, this is a finding.\n\nThe special permissions for the following default groups are not the focus of this requirement and may include a wide range of permissions and properties:\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\nSYSTEM - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nDomain Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nEnterprise Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Delete all child objects, Special permissions\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When directory service database objects do not have appropriate access control permissions, it may be possible for malicious users to create, read, update, or delete the objects and degrade or destroy the integrity of the data. When the directory service is used for identification, authentication, or authorization functions, a compromise of the database objects could lead to a compromise of all systems relying on the directory service.\n\nFor Active Directory (AD), the Group Policy objects require special attention. In a distributed administration model (i.e., help desk), Group Policy objects are more likely to have access permissions changed from the secure defaults. If inappropriate access permissions are defined for Group Policy objects, this could allow an intruder to change the security policy applied to all domain client computers (workstations and servers).","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"2784","uuid":"7d3da23e-f047-43b5-9d23-361804e3cfab","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 132FEFF0D5045A63E09AD657F0C79FBC0CEE4C3C\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Group Policy objects must have proper access control permissions.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254394","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254394","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254394","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254394r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254394","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000100","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Domain Controllers Organizational Unit (OU) object must have the proper access control permissions.","fix_text":"Limit the permissions on the Domain Controllers OU to restrict changes to System, Domain Admins, Enterprise Admins and Administrators.\n\nThe default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nDomains supporting Microsoft Exchange will have additional Exchange related permissions on the Domain Controllers OU. These may include some change related permissions.\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\n\nSELF - Special permissions\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Authenticated Users are Read types.\n\nSYSTEM - Full Control\n\nDomain Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Admins - Full Control\n\nKey Admins - Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Key Admins - Special permissions\n\nAdministrators - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nPre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access - Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Pre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access are Read types.\n\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the permissions on the Domain Controllers OU.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nSelect \"Advanced Features\" in the \"View\" menu if not previously selected.\n\nSelect the \"Domain Controllers\" OU (folder in folder icon).\n\nRight-click and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nIf the permissions on the Domain Controllers OU do not restrict changes to System, Domain Admins, Enterprise Admins and Administrators, this is a finding.\n\nThe default permissions listed below satisfy this requirement.\n\nDomains supporting Microsoft Exchange will have additional Exchange related permissions on the Domain Controllers OU. These may include some change related permissions and are not a finding.\n\nThe permissions shown are at the summary level. More detailed permissions can be viewed by selecting the \"Advanced\" button, the desired Permission entry, and the \"View\" or \"Edit\" button.\n\nExcept where noted otherwise, the special permissions may include a wide range of permissions and properties and are acceptable for this requirement.\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\n\nSELF - Special permissions\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Authenticated Users are Read types.\n\nIf detailed permissions include any Create, Delete, Modify, or Write Permissions or Properties, this is a finding.\n\nSYSTEM - Full Control\n\nDomain Admins - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Admins - Full Control\n\nKey Admins - Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Key Admins - Special permissions\n\nAdministrators - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nPre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access - Special permissions\n\nThe Special permissions for Pre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access are Read types.\n\nIf detailed permissions include any Create, Delete, Modify, or Write Permissions or Properties, this is a finding.\n\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When Active Directory objects do not have appropriate access control permissions, it may be possible for malicious users to create, read, update, or delete the objects and degrade or destroy the integrity of the data. When the directory service is used for identification, authentication, or authorization functions, a compromise of the database objects could lead to a compromise of all systems that rely on the directory service.\n\nThe Domain Controllers OU object requires special attention as the Domain Controllers are central to the configuration and management of the domain. Inappropriate access permissions defined for the Domain Controllers OU could allow an intruder or unauthorized personnel to make changes that could lead to the compromise of the domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3598","uuid":"f9c23c65-1d72-4ab0-b046-edd2d14cce3e","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1406EB3652E34E307B3FB3D719949D50C606A345\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Domain Controllers Organizational Unit (OU) object must have the proper access control permissions.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254395","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254395","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254395","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254395r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254395","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000110","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 organization created Active Directory Organizational Unit (OU) objects must have proper access control permissions.","fix_text":"Maintain the Allow type permissions on domain-defined OUs to be at least as restrictive as the defaults below.\n\nDocument any additional permissions above Read with the ISSO if an approved distributed administration model (help desk or other user support staff) is implemented.\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\n\nSelf - Special permissions\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Authenticated Users are Read type.\n\nSYSTEM - Full Control\n\nDomain Admins - Full Control\n\nEnterprise Admins - Full Control\n\nKey Admins - Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Key Admins - Special permissions\n\nAdministrators - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nPre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access - Special permissions\n\nThe special permissions for Pre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access are for Read types.\n\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the permissions on domain-defined OUs.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nFor each OU that is defined (folder in folder icon) excluding the Domain Controllers OU:\n\nRight-click the OU and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nIf the Allow type permissions on the OU are not at least as restrictive as those below, this is a finding.\n\nThe permissions shown are at the summary level. More detailed permissions can be viewed by selecting the \"Advanced\" button, the desired Permission entry, and the \"Edit\" or \"View\" button.\n\nExcept where noted otherwise, the special permissions may include a wide range of permissions and properties and are acceptable for this requirement.\n\nCREATOR OWNER - Special permissions\n\nSelf - Special permissions\n\nAuthenticated Users - Read, Special permissions\n\nThe Special permissions for Authenticated Users are Read type. If detailed permissions include any Create, Delete, Modify, or Write Permissions or Properties, this is a finding.\n\nSYSTEM - Full Control\n\nDomain Admins - Full Control\n\nEnterprise Admins - Full Control\n\nKey Admins - Special permissions\n\nEnterprise Key Admins - Special permissions\n\nAdministrators - Read, Write, Create all child objects, Generate resultant set of policy (logging), Generate resultant set of policy (planning), Special permissions\n\nPre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access - Special permissions\n\nThe Special permissions for Pre-Windows 2000 Compatible Access are for Read types. If detailed permissions include any Create, Delete, Modify, or Write Permissions or Properties, this is a finding.\n\nENTERPRISE DOMAIN CONTROLLERS - Read, Special permissions\n\nIf an Information System Security Officer (ISSO)-approved distributed administration model (help desk or other user support staff) is implemented, permissions above Read may be allowed for groups documented by the ISSO.\n\nIf any OU with improper permissions includes identification or authentication data (e.g., accounts, passwords, or password hash data) used by systems to determine access control, the severity is CAT I (e.g., OUs that include user accounts, including service/application accounts).\n\nIf an OU with improper permissions does not include identification and authentication data used by systems to determine access control, the severity is CAT II (e.g., Workstation, Printer OUs).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When directory service database objects do not have appropriate access control permissions, it may be possible for malicious users to create, read, update, or delete the objects and degrade or destroy the integrity of the data. When the directory service is used for identification, authentication, or authorization functions, a compromise of the database objects could lead to a compromise of all systems that rely on the directory service.\n\nFor Active Directory, the OU objects require special attention. In a distributed administration model (i.e., help desk), OU objects are more likely to have access permissions changed from the secure defaults. If inappropriate access permissions are defined for OU objects, it could allow an intruder to add or delete users in the OU. This could result in unauthorized access to data or a denial of service (DoS) to authorized users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"4809","uuid":"80c7e66e-6aeb-4d35-b63e-a1d851778f7d","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254396","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254396","title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254396","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","rule_id_src":"SV-254396r1137695_rule","rule_id":"SV-254396","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000120","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 data files owned by users must be on a different logical partition from the directory server data files.","fix_text":"Move shares used to store files owned by users to a different logical partition than the directory server data files.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nRun \"Regedit\".\n\nNavigate to \"HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\NTDS\\Parameters\".\n\nNote the directory locations in the values for \"DSA Database file\".\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt\".\n\nEnter \"net share\".\n\nNote the logical drive(s) or file system partition for any organization-created data shares.\n\nIgnore system shares (e.g., NETLOGON, SYSVOL, and administrative shares ending in $). User shares that are hidden (ending with $) must not be ignored.\n\nIf user shares are located on the same logical partition as the directory server data files, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When directory service data files, especially for directories used for identification, authentication, or authorization, reside on the same logical partition as user-owned files, the directory service data may be more vulnerable to unauthorized access or other availability compromises. Directory service and user-owned data files sharing a partition may be configured with less restrictive permissions in order to allow access to the user data. \n\nThe directory service may be vulnerable to a denial of service attack when user-owned files on a common partition are expanded to an extent preventing the directory service from acquiring more space for directory or audit data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001090"],"reference_identifier":"9122","uuid":"ee24134c-6564-436f-8bdb-87b2f0982ca1","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 475781026F8E4431F0D60109EA898DD12A28B156\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 data files owned by users must be on a different logical partition from the directory server data files.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254397","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254397","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254397","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254397r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254397","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000130","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must run on a machine dedicated to that function.","fix_text":"Remove additional roles or applications such as web, database, and email from the domain controller.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers, it is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the installed roles the domain controller is supporting.\n\nStart \"Server Manager\".\n\nSelect \"AD DS\" in the left pane and the server name under \"Servers\" to the right.\n\nSelect \"Add (or Remove) Roles and Features\" from \"Tasks\" in the \"Roles and Features\" section. (Cancel before any changes are made.)\n\nDetermine if any additional server roles are installed. A basic domain controller setup will include the following:\n\n- Active Directory Domain Services\n- DNS Server\n- File and Storage Services\n\nIf any roles not requiring installation on a domain controller are installed, this is a finding. \n\nA Domain Name System (DNS) server integrated with the directory server (e.g., AD-integrated DNS) is an acceptable application. However, the DNS server must comply with the DNS STIG security requirements.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\n\nReview installed applications.\n\nIf any applications are installed that are not required for the domain controller, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Executing application servers on the same host machine with a directory server may substantially weaken the security of the directory server. Web or database server applications usually require the addition of many programs and accounts, increasing the attack surface of the computer. \n\nSome applications require the addition of privileged accounts, providing potential sources of compromise. Some applications (such as Microsoft Exchange) may require the use of network ports or services conflicting with the directory server. In this case, nonstandard ports might be selected, and this could interfere with intrusion detection or prevention services.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"6365","uuid":"fca078c7-f81f-4324-a3df-e0dd50ce6094","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 21A77A4EDD0A12A58FA71C393E51641DD6C0FDED\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must run on a machine dedicated to that function.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254398","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254398","title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254398","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000396-GPOS-00176","rule_id_src":"SV-254398r987791_rule","rule_id":"SV-254398","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000140","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must use separate, NSA-approved (Type 1) cryptography to protect the directory data in transit for directory service implementations at a classified confidentiality level when replication data traverses a network cleared to a lower level than the data.","fix_text":"Configure NSA-approved (Type 1) cryptography to protect the directory data in transit for directory service implementations at a classified confidentiality level that transfer replication data through a network cleared to a lower level than the data.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the organization network diagram(s) or documentation to determine the level of classification for the network(s) over which replication data is transmitted.\n\nDetermine the classification level of the Windows domain controller.\n\nIf the classification level of the Windows domain controller is higher than the level of the networks, review the organization network diagram(s) and directory implementation documentation to determine if NSA-approved encryption is used to protect the replication network traffic.\n\nIf the classification level of the Windows domain controller is higher than the level of the network traversed and NSA-approved encryption is not used, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Directory data that is not appropriately encrypted is subject to compromise. Commercial-grade encryption does not provide adequate protection when the classification level of directory data in transit is higher than the level of the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002450"],"reference_identifier":"8445","uuid":"7add5de9-b527-4a40-ad4f-f4d26f71b73d","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254399","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254399","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254399","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254399r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254399","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000150","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 directory data (outside the root DSE) of a nonpublic directory must be configured to prevent anonymous access.","fix_text":"Configure directory data (outside the root DSE) of a nonpublic directory to prevent anonymous access.\n\nFor AD, there are multiple configuration items that could enable anonymous access.\n\nChanging the access permissions on the domain naming context object (from the secure defaults) could enable anonymous access. If the check procedures indicate this is the cause, the process that was used to change the permissions must be reversed. This could have been through the Windows Support Tools ADSI Edit console (adsiedit.msc).\n\nThe dsHeuristics option is used. This is addressed in check V-8555 in the AD Forest STIG.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt\" (not elevated).\n\nRun \"ldp.exe\".\n\nFrom the \"Connection menu\", select \"Bind\".\n\nClear the User, Password, and Domain fields.\n\nSelect \"Simple bind\" for the Bind type and click \"OK\".\n\nConfirmation of anonymous access will be displayed at the end:\n\nres = ldap_simple_bind_s\nAuthenticated as: 'NT AUTHORITY\\ANONYMOUS LOGON'\n\nFrom the \"Browse\" menu, select \"Search\".\n\nIn the Search dialog, enter the DN of the domain naming context (generally something like \"dc=disaost,dc=mil\") in the Base DN field.\n\nClear the Attributes field and select \"Run\".\n\nError messages must display related to Bind and user not authenticated.\n\nIf attribute data is displayed, anonymous access is enabled to the domain naming context and this is a finding.\n\nThe following network controls allow the finding severity to be downgraded to a CAT II since these measures lower the risk associated with anonymous access.\n\nNetwork hardware ports at the site are subject to 802.1x authentication or MAC address restrictions. \n\nPremise firewall or host restrictions prevent access to ports 389, 636, 3268, and 3269 from client hosts not explicitly identified by domain (.mil) or IP address.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To the extent that anonymous access to directory data (outside the root DSE) is permitted, read access control of the data is effectively disabled. If other means of controlling access (such as network restrictions) are compromised, there may be nothing else to protect the confidentiality of sensitive directory data.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9347","uuid":"cb187fb6-ef01-40a0-8af7-be096a86ae6d","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 732B11AEE76DA0AB847B69672A2362017F3C0967\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 directory data (outside the root DSE) of a nonpublic directory must be configured to prevent anonymous access.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254400","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254400","title":"SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254400","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072","rule_id_src":"SV-254400r970703_rule","rule_id":"SV-254400","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000160","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 directory service must be configured to terminate LDAP-based network connections to the directory server after five minutes of inactivity.","fix_text":"Configure the directory service to terminate LDAP-based network connections to the directory server after 5 minutes of inactivity.\n\nOpen an elevated \"Command prompt\" (run as administrator).\n\nEnter \"ntdsutil\".\n\nAt the \"ntdsutil:\" prompt, enter \"LDAP policies\".\n\nAt the \"ldap policy:\" prompt, enter \"connections\".\n\nAt the \"server connections:\" prompt, enter \"connect to server [host-name]\" (where [host-name] is the computer name of the domain controller).\n\nAt the \"server connections:\" prompt, enter \"q\".\n\nAt the \"ldap policy:\" prompt, enter \"Set MaxConnIdleTime to 300\".\n\nEnter \"Commit Changes\" to save.\n\nEnter \"Show values\" to verify changes.\n\nEnter \"q\" at the \"ldap policy:\" and \"ntdsutil:\" prompts to exit.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nOpen an elevated \"Command Prompt\" (run as administrator).\n\nEnter \"ntdsutil\".\n\nAt the \"ntdsutil:\" prompt, enter \"LDAP policies\".\n\nAt the \"ldap policy:\" prompt, enter \"connections\".\n\nAt the \"server connections:\" prompt, enter \"connect to server [host-name]\"\n(where [host-name] is the computer name of the domain controller).\n\nAt the \"server connections:\" prompt, enter \"q\".\n\nAt the \"ldap policy:\" prompt, enter \"show values\". \n\nIf the value for MaxConnIdleTime is greater than \"300\" (5 minutes) or is not specified, this is a finding.\n\nEnter \"q\" at the \"ldap policy:\" and \"ntdsutil:\" prompts to exit.\n\nAlternately, Dsquery can be used to display MaxConnIdleTime:\n\nOpen \"Command Prompt (Admin)\".\nEnter the following command (on a single line).\n\ndsquery * \"cn=Default Query Policy,cn=Query-Policies,cn=Directory Service, cn=Windows NT,cn=Services,cn=Configuration,dc=[forest-name]\" -attr LDAPAdminLimits \n\nThe quotes are required and dc=[forest-name] is the fully qualified LDAP name of the domain being reviewed (e.g., dc=disaost,dc=mil).\n\nIf the results do not specify a \"MaxConnIdleTime\" or it has a value greater than \"300\" (5 minutes), this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The failure to terminate inactive network connections increases the risk of a successful attack on the directory server. The longer an established session is in progress, the more time an attacker has to hijack the session, implement a means to passively intercept data, or compromise any protections on client access. For example, if an attacker gains control of a client computer, an existing (already authenticated) session with the directory server could allow access to the directory. The lack of confidentiality protection in LDAP-based sessions increases exposure to this vulnerability.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000163-GPOS-00072, SRG-OS-000279-GPOS-00109","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001133","CCI-002361"],"reference_identifier":"7374","uuid":"dcf8e32e-ce65-4d49-8b8d-6a83f222caab","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1FDA7D8FA6A5092BA2D19FBAC13679F3C2EE27E5\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 directory service must be configured to terminate LDAP-based network connections to the directory server after five minutes of inactivity.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254401","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254401","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254401","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-254401r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-254401","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000170","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Group Policy objects must be configured with proper audit settings.","fix_text":"Configure the audit settings for Group Policy objects to include the following:\n\nThis can be done at the Policy level in Active Directory to apply to all group policies.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nSelect \"Advanced Features\" from the \"View\" Menu.\n\nNavigate to [Domain] >> System >> Policies in the left panel.\n\nRight-click \"Policies\", select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\".\n\nSelect the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nApplies to - This object and all descendant objects or Descendant groupPolicyContainer objects\n\nThe three Success types listed below are defaults inherited from the Parent Object. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special (Permissions: Write all properties, Modify permissions; Properties: all \"Write\" type selected)\nInherited from - Parent Object\nApplies to - Descendant groupPolicyContainer objects\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - blank (Permissions: none selected; Properties: one instance - Write gPLink, one instance - Write gPOptions)\nInherited from - Parent Object\nApplies to - Descendant Organization Unit Objects","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for all Group Policy objects.\n\nOpen \"Group Policy Management\" (available from various menus or run \"gpmc.msc\").\n\nNavigate to \"Group Policy Objects\" in the domain being reviewed (Forest >> Domains >> Domain).\n\nFor each Group Policy object:\n\nSelect the Group Policy object item in the left pane.\n\nSelect the \"Delegation\" tab in the right pane.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\".\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" again and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings for any Group Policy object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nApplies to - This object and all descendant objects or Descendant groupPolicyContainer objects\n\nThe three Success types listed below are defaults inherited from the Parent Object. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special (Permissions: Write all properties, Modify permissions; Properties: all \"Write\" type selected)\nInherited from - Parent Object\nApplies to - Descendant groupPolicyContainer objects\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - blank (Permissions: none selected; Properties: one instance - Write gPLink, one instance - Write gPOptions)\nInherited from - Parent Object\nApplies to - Descendant Organization Unit Objects","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes Group Policy objects. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"9041","uuid":"48d4f7c7-2def-4ad0-982e-24302dd0fea4","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9D2135305039EB0965E71735F36D1068B816429C\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Group Policy objects must be configured with proper audit settings.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254402","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254402","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254402","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-254402r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-254402","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000180","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Domain object must be configured with proper audit settings.","fix_text":"Open \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the domain name and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nConfigure the audit settings for Domain object to include the following:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - Special\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Domain Users\nAccess - All extended rights\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Administrators\nAccess - All extended rights\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Permissions: Write all properties, Modify permissions, Modify owner.)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for the Domain object.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the domain name and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings on the Domain object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - Special\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Domain Users\nAccess - All extended rights\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Administrators\nAccess - All extended rights\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Permissions: Write all properties, Modify permissions, Modify owner)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes the Domain object. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"3770","uuid":"5bcb2b6e-d004-49b9-869a-e1277ff4c5b0","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254403","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254403","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254403","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-254403r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-254403","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000190","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Infrastructure object must be configured with proper audit settings.","fix_text":"Open \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"Infrastructure\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nConfigure the audit settings for Infrastructure object to include the following:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\n(Access - Special = Permissions: Write all properties, All extended rights, Change infrastructure master)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for Infrastructure object.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"Infrastructure\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings on the Infrastructure object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\n(Access - Special = Permissions: Write all properties, All extended rights, Change infrastructure master)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes the Infrastructure object. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"4962","uuid":"563024c6-fe32-4e76-803c-60b2efa1d0ca","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0D91454754347E9A4E2EFB8554258EA69DADC7F9\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Infrastructure object must be configured with proper audit settings.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254404","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254404","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254404","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-254404r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-254404","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000200","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Domain Controllers Organizational Unit (OU) object must be configured with proper audit settings.","fix_text":"Open \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the \"Domain Controllers OU\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"Domain Controllers OU\" object and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nConfigure the audit settings for Domain Controllers OU object to include the following:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Permissions: all create, delete and modify permissions)\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Write all properties\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object and all descendant objects\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)\nApplies to - Descendant Organizational Unit objects","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for the Domain Controller OU object.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect the \"Domain Controllers OU\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"Domain Controllers OU\" object and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings on the Domain Controllers OU object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object and all descendant objects\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Permissions: all create, delete and modify permissions)\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Write all properties\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object and all descendant objects\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)\nApplies to - Descendant Organizational Unit objects","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes the Domain Controller OU object. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"1477","uuid":"ce23bd8c-c3a0-47f6-82fa-a1702cd24743","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C8AF8E4FA7DDCFACF13E328B526746DE004B9CD2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Active Directory Domain Controllers Organizational Unit (OU) object must be configured with proper audit settings.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254405","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254405","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254405","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-254405r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-254405","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000210","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory AdminSDHolder object must be configured with proper audit settings.","fix_text":"Open \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect \"System\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"AdminSDHolder\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nConfigure the audit settings for AdminSDHolder object to include the following:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Write all properties, Modify permissions, Modify owner)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)\nApplies to - Descendant Organizational Unit objects","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for the \"AdminSDHolder\" object.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect \"System\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"AdminSDHolder\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings on the \"AdminSDHolder\" object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\nApplies to - This object only\n(Access - Special = Write all properties, Modify permissions, Modify owner)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)\nApplies to - Descendant Organizational Unit objects","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes the AdminSDHolder object. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"6831","uuid":"72c9d9cd-8f87-4815-a9ea-a9d2dec73221","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B8793C3730AA154D6135B5C96931CD4D17806E6C\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Active Directory AdminSDHolder object must be configured with proper audit settings.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254406","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254406","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254406","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-254406r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-254406","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000220","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory RID Manager$ object must be configured with proper audit settings.","fix_text":"Open \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect \"System\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"RID Manager$\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nConfigure the audit settings for RID Manager$ object to include the following:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\n (Access - Special = Write all properties, All extended rights, Change RID master)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview the auditing configuration for the \"RID Manager$\" object.\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nEnsure \"Advanced Features\" is selected in the \"View\" menu.\n\nSelect \"System\" under the domain being reviewed in the left pane.\n\nRight-click the \"RID Manager$\" object in the right pane and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSelect \"Advanced\" and then the \"Auditing\" tab.\n\nIf the audit settings on the \"RID Manager$\" object are not at least as inclusive as those below, this is a finding:\n\nType - Fail\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Full Control\nInherited from - None\n\nThe success types listed below are defaults. Where Special is listed in the summary screens for Access, detailed Permissions are provided for reference. Various Properties selections may also exist by default.\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - Special\nInherited from - None\n (Access - Special = Write all properties, All extended rights, Change RID master)\n\nTwo instances with the following summary information will be listed:\n\nType - Success\nPrincipal - Everyone\nAccess - (blank)\nInherited from - (CN of domain)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"When inappropriate audit settings are configured for directory service database objects, it may be possible for a user or process to update the data without generating any tracking data. The impact of missing audit data is related to the type of object. A failure to capture audit data for objects used by identification, authentication, or authorization functions could degrade or eliminate the ability to track changes to access policy for systems or data. \n\nFor Active Directory (AD), there are a number of critical object types in the domain naming context of the AD database for which auditing is essential. This includes the RID Manager$ object. Because changes to these objects can significantly impact access controls or the availability of systems, the absence of auditing data makes it impossible to identify the source of changes that impact the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data and systems throughout an AD domain. The lack of proper auditing can result in insufficient forensic evidence needed to investigate an incident and prosecute the intruder.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"4135","uuid":"7c639fa5-e211-4d7e-8840-e230edbf4bcf","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 66DFA0A453E4344A3701DEFD3E1DB55CB8255F2D\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Active Directory RID Manager$ object must be configured with proper audit settings.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254407","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254407","title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254407","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004","rule_id_src":"SV-254407r958368_rule","rule_id":"SV-254407","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000230","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit Account Management - Computer Account Management successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> Account Management >> Audit Computer Account Management with Success selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nSecurity Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nAccount Management >> Computer Account Management - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nComputer Account Management records events such as creating, changing, deleting, renaming, disabling, or enabling computer accounts.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000004-GPOS-00004, SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089, SRG-OS-000240-GPOS-00090, SRG-OS-000241-GPOS-00091, SRG-OS-000303-GPOS-00120, SRG-OS-000476-GPOS-00221","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000018","CCI-000172","CCI-001403","CCI-001404","CCI-001405","CCI-002130"],"reference_identifier":"6691","uuid":"fdfbbf5d-3fda-4750-8a66-7cadb1b5cbcb","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5103B5FE85356DDBE4706F82A364AD437893B630\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit Account Management - Computer Account Management successes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254408","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254408","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254408","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-254408r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-254408","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000240","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit DS Access - Directory Service Access successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> DS Access >> Directory Service Access with Success selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nSecurity Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nDS Access >> Directory Service Access - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Directory Service Access records events related to users accessing an Active Directory object.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"4633","uuid":"2d9900d6-35b5-4fd4-8408-a2d3293e8d92","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FD00984BF4A88CE1F6C6B64D2AE9DA4A169A3056\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit DS Access - Directory Service Access successes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254409","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254409","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254409","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-254409r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-254409","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000250","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit DS Access - Directory Service Access failures.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> DS Access >> Directory Service Access with \"Failure\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nSecurity Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nDS Access >> Directory Service Access - Failure","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Directory Service Access records events related to users accessing an Active Directory object.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"2827","uuid":"035117ba-ad7e-402f-b990-a73f4139e469","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F12DAA073EAD3FDE3CC759E48BBB763E281C7AAE\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit DS Access - Directory Service Access failures.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254410","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254410","title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254410","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","rule_id_src":"SV-254410r958732_rule","rule_id":"SV-254410","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000260","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit DS Access - Directory Service Changes successes.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Advanced Audit Policy Configuration >> System Audit Policies >> DS Access >> Directory Service Changes with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nSecurity Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN22-SO-000050) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the \"AuditPol\" tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" or a \"Command Prompt\" with elevated privileges (\"Run as administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the \"AuditPol\" settings with the following:\n\nIf the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nDS Access >> Directory Service Changes - Success","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Directory Service Changes records events related to changes made to objects in Active Directory Domain Services.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127, SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203, SRG-OS-000463-GPOS-00207, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-002234"],"reference_identifier":"3373","uuid":"1f1feecc-d74c-496f-837a-6635ddd37fc0","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 748BC88A1F41FF8B625658F61344A748B6F6F529\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to audit DS Access - Directory Service Changes successes.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254412","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254412","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254412","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-254412r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-254412","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000280","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must have a PKI server certificate.","fix_text":"Obtain a server certificate for the domain controller.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"Add/Remove Snap-in\" from the \"File\" menu.\n\nSelect \"Certificates\" in the left pane and click \"Add >\".\n\nSelect \"Computer Account\" and click \"Next\".\n\nSelect the appropriate option for \"Select the computer you want this snap-in to manage\" and click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nSelect and expand the Certificates (Local Computer) entry in the left pane.\n\nSelect and expand the Personal entry in the left pane.\n\nSelect the Certificates entry in the left pane.\n\nIf no certificate for the domain controller exists in the right pane, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Domain controllers are part of the chain of trust for PKI authentications. Without the appropriate certificate, the authenticity of the domain controller cannot be verified. Domain controllers must have a server certificate to establish authenticity as part of PKI authentications in the domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"9768","uuid":"17884220-6da5-42a7-9d94-856b46fc685c","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 749E6CC85E5F4CB324BE9E0585CF5E5D23900ED1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must have a PKI server certificate.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254413","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254413","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254413","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-254413r1153446_rule","rule_id":"SV-254413","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000290","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 domain controller PKI certificates must be issued by the DOD PKI or an approved External Certificate Authority (ECA).","fix_text":"Obtain a server certificate for the domain controller issued by the DOD PKI or an approved ECA.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"Add/Remove Snap-in\" from the \"File\" menu.\n\nSelect \"Certificates\" in the left pane, and then click \"Add >\".\n\nSelect \"Computer Account\", and then click \"Next\".\n\nSelect the appropriate option for \"Select the computer you want this snap-in to manage\", and then click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nSelect and expand the \"Certificates (Local Computer)\" entry in the left pane.\n\nSelect and expand the \"Personal\" entry in the left pane.\n\nSelect the \"Certificates\" entry in the left pane.\n\nIn the right pane, examine the \"Issued By\" field for the certificate to determine the issuing CA.\n\nIf the \"Issued By\" field of the PKI certificate being used by the domain controller does not indicate the issuing CA is part of the DOD PKI or an approved ECA, this is a finding.\n\nIf the certificates in use are issued by a CA authorized by the Component's CIO, this is a CAT II finding.\n\nThere are multiple sources from which lists of valid DOD CAs and approved ECAs can be obtained: \n\nThe Global Directory Service (GDS) website provides an online source. The address for this site is https://crl.gds.disa.mil.\n\nDOD Public Key Enablement (PKE) Engineering Support maintains the InstallRoot utility to manage DOD supported root certificates on Windows computers, which includes a list of authorized CAs. The utility package can be downloaded from the PKI and PKE Tools page on Cyber Exchange: https://www.cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A PKI implementation depends on the practices established by the Certificate Authority (CA) to ensure the implementation is secure. Without proper practices, the certificates issued by a CA have limited value in authentication functions. The use of multiple CAs from separate PKI implementations results in interoperability issues. If servers and clients do not have a common set of root CA certificates, they are not able to authenticate each other.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"3164","uuid":"c235e134-594a-4be4-aa89-8c7f58d88f6f","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 721DBAB19236D6F58FE79A012700CAD47A73267D\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 domain controller PKI certificates must be issued by the DOD PKI or an approved External Certificate Authority (ECA).' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254414","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254414","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254414","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-254414r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-254414","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000300","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 PKI certificates associated with user accounts must be issued by a DoD PKI or an approved External Certificate Authority (ECA).","fix_text":"Map user accounts to PKI certificates using the appropriate User Principal Name (UPN) for the network. See PKE documentation for details.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nReview user account mappings to PKI certificates.\n\nOpen \"Windows PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-ADUser -Filter * | FT Name, UserPrincipalName, Enabled\".\n\nExclude disabled accounts (e.g., DefaultAccount, Guest) and the krbtgt account.\n\nIf the User Principal Name (UPN) is not in the format of an individual's identifier for the certificate type and for the appropriate domain suffix, this is a finding.\n\nFor standard NIPRNet certificates, the individual's identifier is in the format of an Electronic Data Interchange - Personnel Identifier (EDI-PI).\n\nAlt Tokens and other certificates may use a different UPN format than the EDI-PI which vary by organization. Verified these with the organization.\n\nNIPRNet Example:\n\nName - User Principal Name\nUser1 - 1234567890@mil\n\nSee PKE documentation for other network domain suffixes.\n\nIf the mappings are to certificates issued by a CA authorized by the Component's CIO, this is a CAT II finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A PKI implementation depends on the practices established by the Certificate Authority (CA) to ensure the implementation is secure. Without proper practices, the certificates issued by a CA have limited value in authentication functions.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034, SRG-OS-000403-GPOS-00182","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185"],"reference_identifier":"3576","uuid":"35a57504-60bf-411b-97e8-f9665dbb7d2a","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 21641ABEA6F04C58FB253FF3E90D7EA78C04DB82\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 PKI certificates associated with user accounts must be issued by a DoD PKI or an approved External Certificate Authority (ECA).' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254415","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254415","title":"SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254415","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052","rule_id_src":"SV-254415r1081074_rule","rule_id":"SV-254415","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000310","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Active Directory user accounts, including administrators, must be configured to require the use of a Common Access Card (CAC), Personal Identity Verification (PIV)-compliant hardware token, or Alternate Logon Token (ALT) for user authentication.","fix_text":"Configure all user accounts, including administrator accounts, in Active Directory to enable the option \"Smart card is required for interactive logon\".\n\nRun \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\"):\n\nSelect the OU where the user accounts are located. (By default this is the Users node; however, accounts may be under other organization-defined OUs.)\n\nRight-click the user account and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Account\" tab.\n\nCheck \"Smart card is required for interactive logon\" in the \"Account Options\" area.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter the following:\n\n\"Get-ADUser -Filter {(Enabled -eq $True) -and (SmartcardLogonRequired -eq $False)} | FT Name\"\n(\"DistinguishedName\" may be substituted for \"Name\" for more detailed output.)\n\nIf any user accounts, including administrators, are listed, this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nTo view sample accounts in \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\"):\n\nSelect the Organizational Unit (OU) where the user accounts are located. (By default, this is the Users node; however, accounts may be under other organization-defined OUs.)\n\nRight-click the sample user account and select \"Properties\".\n\nSelect the \"Account\" tab.\n\nIf any user accounts, including administrators, do not have \"Smart card is required for interactive logon\" checked in the \"Account Options\" area, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Smart cards such as the CAC support a two-factor authentication technique. This provides a higher level of trust in the asserted identity than use of the username and password for authentication.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000105-GPOS-00052, SRG-OS-000106-GPOS-00053, SRG-OS-000107-GPOS-00054, SRG-OS-000108-GPOS-00055, SRG-OS-000375-GPOS-00160","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000776","CCI-000767","CCI-000768","CCI-001948"],"reference_identifier":"2050","uuid":"a719abaf-324c-457f-92d9-34524e50ebcd","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CA43EC26029019CFAA0A5FAB986155013D6D02CD\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Active Directory user accounts, including administrators, must be configured to require the use of a Common Access Card (CAC), Personal Identity Verification (PIV)-compliant hardware token, or Alternate Logon Token (ALT) for user authentication.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254416","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254416","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254416","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-254416r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-254416","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000320","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must require LDAP access signing.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Domain controller: LDAP server signing requirements to \"Require signing\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\NTDS\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: LDAPServerIntegrity\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unsigned network traffic is susceptible to man-in-the-middle attacks, where an intruder captures packets between the server and the client and modifies them before forwarding them to the client. In the case of an LDAP server, this means that an attacker could cause a client to make decisions based on false records from the LDAP directory. The risk of an attacker pulling this off can be decreased by implementing strong physical security measures to protect the network infrastructure. Furthermore, implementing Internet Protocol security (IPsec) authentication header mode (AH), which performs mutual authentication and packet integrity for Internet Protocol (IP) traffic, can make all types of man-in-the-middle attacks extremely difficult.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"6417","uuid":"1db2ab2d-602c-41f0-a837-1f120d246e6d","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 53AF914A345A3EAE76638CFCF4B8186739F6C2D4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must require LDAP access signing.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254417","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254417","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254417","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254417r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254417","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000330","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must be configured to allow reset of machine account passwords.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Domain controller: Refuse machine account password changes to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RefusePasswordChange\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Enabling this setting on all domain controllers in a domain prevents domain members from changing their computer account passwords. If these passwords are weak or compromised, the inability to change them may leave these computers vulnerable.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"6350","uuid":"e5f8a6b2-895f-4e8e-8f29-87e4cb3b1f07","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 62C402149597D07B1CC3824F725D4E439317E6B9\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 domain controllers must be configured to allow reset of machine account passwords.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254418","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254418","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254418","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254418r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254418","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000340","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators, Authenticated Users, and \nEnterprise Domain Controllers groups on domain controllers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Access this computer from the network to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators\n- Authenticated Users\n- Enterprise Domain Controllers","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Access this computer from the network\" right, this is a finding.\n\n- Administrators\n- Authenticated Users\n- Enterprise Domain Controllers\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeNetworkLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\nS-1-5-11 (Authenticated Users)\nS-1-5-9 (Enterprise Domain Controllers)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access this computer from the network\" right may access resources on the system, and this right must be limited to those requiring it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"9397","uuid":"7414e36d-a229-48e8-ad5e-3d52f1092597","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 05DB1C99D6461591AED02976330DA8FF59AA25EB\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators, Authenticated Users, and \nEnterprise Domain Controllers groups on domain controllers.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254419","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254419","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254419","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254419r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254419","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000350","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Add workstations to domain user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group on domain controllers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Add workstations to domain to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. It is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Add workstations to domain\" right, this is a finding.\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeMachineAccountPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Add workstations to domain\" right may add computers to a domain. This could result in unapproved or incorrectly configured systems being added to a domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"3282","uuid":"9bdf004a-d44f-4e1f-bab3-a4264745dccd","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2404E62962E32C881B2F1756BCABD8EA60DB8893\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Add workstations to domain user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group on domain controllers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254420","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254420","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254420","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254420r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254420","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000360","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group on domain controllers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers, it is NA for other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right, this is a finding.\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeRemoteInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Allow log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right can access a system through Remote Desktop.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"2739","uuid":"db5034c7-8017-439f-9a3c-a214676197e0","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254421","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254421","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254421","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254421r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254421","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000370","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny access to this computer from the network user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Deny access to this computer from the network to include the following:\n\n- Guests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyNetworkLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on from the network.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"1560","uuid":"5c7a0ce9-6c32-480e-85ff-b0ae41c73346","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 0D51C95C66C91D90CA2CCD846A35527AFFA1AE61\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Deny access to this computer from the network user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254422","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254422","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254422","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254422r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254422","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000380","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a batch job user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Deny log on as a batch job to include the following:\n\n- Guests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SID(s) are not defined for the \"SeDenyBatchLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on to the system as a batch job, such as Task Scheduler.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"6283","uuid":"0eea7f0e-dc2e-415f-8c4a-3bd47c0a5184","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F27722B14BB0320AFAF4E2F24E77A6A5E785C309\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a batch job user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254423","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254423","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254423","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254423r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254423","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000390","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a service user right must be configured to include no accounts or groups (blank) on domain controllers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Deny log on as a service to include no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are defined for the \"Deny log on as a service\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeDenyServiceLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a service\" user right defines accounts that are denied logon as a service.\n\nIncorrect configurations could prevent services from starting and result in a denial of service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"9818","uuid":"8e1443fc-b9c4-4dcf-9afa-a9f4975b33cb","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 187AB9A25427BC626DEACB98C8DE2EF357BE3C4A\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a service user right must be configured to include no accounts or groups (blank) on domain controllers.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254424","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254424","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254424","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254424r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254424","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000400","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on locally user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Deny log on locally to include the following:\n\n- Guests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SID(s) are not defined for the \"SeDenyInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on locally\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on interactively.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"8565","uuid":"c6de551f-05f9-4879-8d40-1ff2fab2d74e","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E6621C913BE9F48466757DDE4C6F0574220C4CA2\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Deny log on locally user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254425","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254425","title":"SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254425","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115","rule_id_src":"SV-254425r958672_rule","rule_id":"SV-254425","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000410","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services to include the following:\n\n- Guests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SID(s) are not defined for the \"SeDenyRemoteInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on using Remote Desktop Services.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002314"],"reference_identifier":"5980","uuid":"7c3e8334-e414-491d-8966-83ac26ede06b","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 1858427C23E7FE12DA4E52C889AB7D4A2C5C1A92\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services user right on domain controllers must be configured to prevent unauthenticated access.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254426","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254426","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254426","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254426r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254426","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000420","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group on domain controllers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to domain controllers. A separate version applies to other systems.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right, this is a finding.\n\n- Administrators\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeEnableDelegationPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right allows the \"Trusted for Delegation\" setting to be changed. This could allow unauthorized users to impersonate other users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8220","uuid":"3131795d-32a4-49af-bb50-875b2dc11e5c","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 6AF9AC9E9F3FE708798C0BA7009142B9C46379F6\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right must only be assigned to the Administrators group on domain controllers.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254427","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254427","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254427","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254427r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254427","rule_version":"WN22-DC-000430","rule_title":"The password for the krbtgt account on a domain must be reset at least every 180 days.","fix_text":"Reset the password for the krbtgt account a least every 180 days. The password must be changed twice to effectively remove the password history. Changing once, waiting for replication to complete and changing again reduces the risk of issues. Changing twice in rapid succession forces clients to re-authenticate (including application services) but is desired if a compromise is suspected.\n\nPowerShell scripts are available to accomplish this such as at the following link:\n\nhttps://gallery.technet.microsoft.com/Reset-the-krbtgt-account-581a9e51\n\nOpen \"Active Directory Users and Computers\" (available from various menus or run \"dsa.msc\").\n\nSelect \"Advanced Features\" in the \"View\" menu if not previously selected.\n\nSelect the \"Users\" node.\n\nRight-click on the krbtgt account and select \"Reset password\".\n\nEnter a password that meets password complexity requirements.\n\nClear the \"User must change password at next logon\" check box.\n\nThe system will automatically change this to a system-generated complex password.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This requirement is applicable to domain controllers; it is NA for other systems. \n\nOpen \"Windows PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"Get-ADUser krbtgt -Property PasswordLastSet\".\n\nIf the \"PasswordLastSet\" date is more than 180 days old, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The krbtgt account acts as a service account for the Kerberos Key Distribution Center (KDC) service. The account and password are created when a domain is created and the password is typically not changed. If the krbtgt account is compromised, attackers can create valid Kerberos Ticket Granting Tickets (TGT).\n\nThe password must be changed twice to effectively remove the password history. Changing once, waiting for replication to complete and the amount of time equal to or greater than the maximum Kerberos ticket lifetime, and changing again reduces the risk of issues.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9647","uuid":"fd7b1b02-e4e4-4321-8bbe-3dabaf165aa9","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: CD5B6DAC5192D47ED15CE4E0076C0B31699696EA\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'The password for the krbtgt account on a domain must be reset at least every 180 days.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254428","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254428","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254428","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254428r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254428","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000010","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must only allow administrators responsible for the member server or standalone or nondomain-joined system to have Administrator rights on the system.","fix_text":"Configure the local \"Administrators\" group to include only administrator groups or accounts responsible for administration of the system.\n\nFor domain-joined member servers, replace the Domain Admins group with a domain member server administrator group. \n\nRemove any standard user accounts.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nOpen \"Computer Management\".\n\nNavigate to \"Groups\" under \"Local Users and Groups\".\n\nReview the local \"Administrators\" group.\n\nOnly administrator groups or accounts responsible for administration of the system may be members of the group.\n\nFor domain-joined member servers, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain member server administrator group.\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the local Administrator group.\n\nIf accounts that do not have responsibility for administration of the system are members of the local Administrators group, this is a finding.\n\nIf the built-in Administrator account or other required administrative accounts are found on the system, this is not a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An account that does not have Administrator duties must not have Administrator rights. Such rights would allow the account to bypass or modify required security restrictions on that machine and make it vulnerable to attack.\n\nSystem administrators must log on to systems using only accounts with the minimum level of authority necessary.\n\nFor domain-joined member servers, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain member server administrator group (see V-243468 in the Active Directory Domain STIG). Restricting highly privileged accounts from the local Administrators group helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the built-in Administrators group.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"1253","uuid":"3155a8a1-3e0e-4722-a64f-ebac7627d1a1","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: AE54C67A763286F82FC9A2EAE81ABB66456E04CD\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must only allow administrators responsible for the member server or standalone or nondomain-joined system to have Administrator rights on the system.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254429","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254429","title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254429","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000134-GPOS-00068","rule_id_src":"SV-254429r958518_rule","rule_id":"SV-254429","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000020","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 local administrator accounts must have their privileged token filtered to prevent elevated privileges from being used over the network on domain-joined member servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> MS Security Guide >> Apply UAC restrictions to local accounts on network logons to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \" SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers. For domain controllers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\n\nValue Name:  LocalAccountTokenFilterPolicy\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)\n\nThis setting may cause issues with some network scanning tools if local administrative accounts are used remotely. Scans must use domain accounts where possible. If a local administrative account must be used, temporarily enabling the privileged token by configuring the registry value to \"1\" may be required.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A compromised local administrator account can provide means for an attacker to move laterally between domain systems.\n\nWith User Account Control enabled, filtering the privileged token for local administrator accounts will prevent the elevated privileges of these accounts from being used over the network.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001084"],"reference_identifier":"6646","uuid":"a078850e-ea3a-448f-9ff6-9248d55e0608","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254430","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254430","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254430","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id_src":"SV-254430r958478_rule","rule_id":"SV-254430","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000030","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 local users on domain-joined member servers must not be enumerated.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Logon >> Enumerate local users on domain-joined computers to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers. For domain controllers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\System\\\n\nValue Name: EnumerateLocalUsers\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The username is one part of logon credentials that could be used to gain access to a system. Preventing the enumeration of users limits this information to authorized personnel.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"reference_identifier":"8157","uuid":"a94cf208-892a-4fc8-ba40-771a0d8a8ba6","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 50A91DEE9CD5AB490D66DE2D4D97785E48BA9C91\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 local users on domain-joined member servers must not be enumerated.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254431","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254431","title":"SRG-OS-000379-GPOS-00164","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254431","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000379-GPOS-00164","rule_id_src":"SV-254431r971545_rule","rule_id":"SV-254431","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000040","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must restrict unauthenticated Remote Procedure Call (RPC) clients from connecting to the RPC server on domain-joined member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Remote Procedure Call >> Restrict Unauthenticated RPC clients to \"Enabled\" with \"Authenticated\" selected.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, it is NA for domain controllers.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\Rpc\\\n\nValue Name:  RestrictRemoteClients\n\nType:  REG_DWORD\nValue:  0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unauthenticated RPC clients may allow anonymous access to sensitive information. Configuring RPC to restrict unauthenticated RPC clients from connecting to the RPC server will prevent anonymous connections.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001967"],"reference_identifier":"3610","uuid":"884ec79f-d582-4b2e-8b18-1b39a10dd290","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254432","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254432","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254432","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254432r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254432","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000050","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must limit the caching of logon credentials to four or less on domain-joined member servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Interactive Logon: Number of previous logons to cache (in case Domain Controller is not available) to \"4\" logons or less.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers. For domain controllers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive:  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:  \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n\nValue Name:  CachedLogonsCount\n\nValue Type:  REG_SZ\nValue:  4 (or less)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The default Windows configuration caches the last logon credentials for users who log on interactively to a system. This feature is provided for system availability reasons, such as the user's machine being disconnected from the network or domain controllers being unavailable. Even though the credential cache is well protected, if a system is attacked, an unauthorized individual may isolate the password to a domain user account using a password-cracking program and gain access to the domain.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"8600","uuid":"0b0db2da-13e0-40b8-8373-9c829b67b30a","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 97543D7A373E1A3D1AB59014E2DF2AFB173AE1C8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must limit the caching of logon credentials to four or less on domain-joined member servers.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254433","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254433","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254433","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254433r1106522_rule","rule_id":"SV-254433","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000060","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must restrict remote calls to the Security Account Manager (SAM) to Administrators on domain-joined member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems.","fix_text":"Navigate to the policy Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Network access: Restrict clients allowed to make remote calls to SAM. \n\nSelect \"Edit Security\" to configure the \"Security descriptor:\".\n\nAdd \"Administrators\" in \"Group or user names:\" if it is not already listed (this is the default).\n\nSelect \"Administrators\" in \"Group or user names:\".\n\nSelect \"Allow\" for \"Remote Access\" in \"Permissions for \"Administrators\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nThe \"Security descriptor:\" must be populated with \"O:BAG:BAD:(A;;RC;;;BA) for the policy to be enforced.\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding. Vendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right. The requirement must be documented and approved by the information system security officer (ISSO).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems; it is NA for domain controllers.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: RestrictRemoteSAM\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: O:BAG:BAD:(A;;RC;;;BA)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The Windows SAM stores users' passwords. Restricting Remote Procedure Call (RPC) connections to the SAM to Administrators helps protect those credentials.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"4087","uuid":"c27a70d4-74b1-42a1-92c3-4e8581f76b5d","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 3DE520BDB5C047168478366950461B66BC3C2B8B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must restrict remote calls to the Security Account Manager (SAM) to Administrators on domain-joined member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254434","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254434","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254434","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254434r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254434","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000070","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Authenticated Users groups on domain-joined member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Access this computer from the network to include only the following accounts or groups:\n\n- Administrators\n- Authenticated Users","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups other than the following are granted the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\n- Administrators\n- Authenticated Users\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs other than the following are granted the \"SeNetworkLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-32-544 (Administrators)\nS-1-5-11 (Authenticated Users)\n\nIf an application requires this user right, this would not be a finding.\n\nVendor documentation must support the requirement for having the user right.\n\nThe requirement must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).\n\nThe application account must meet requirements for application account passwords, such as length (WN22-00-000050) and required frequency of changes (WN22-00-000060).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nAccounts with the \"Access this computer from the network\" user right may access resources on the system, and this right must be limited to those requiring it.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"9879","uuid":"76b3342c-5856-45e8-80a6-85836c30c74c","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E8CBD8A0941BAC1243F1B0510DD2CA215F6ED5B1\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Access this computer from the network user right must only be assigned to the Administrators and Authenticated Users groups on domain-joined member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254435","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254435","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254435","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254435r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254435","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000080","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny access to this computer from the network user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Deny access to this computer from the network to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins group\n- Domain Admins group\n- \"Local account and member of Administrators group\" or \"Local account\" (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests group\n\nNote: These are built-in security groups. \"Local account\" is more restrictive but may cause issues on servers such as systems that provide failover clustering.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins group\n- Domain Admins group\n- \"Local account and member of Administrators group\" or \"Local account\" (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyNetworkLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nS-1-5-root domain-519 (Enterprise Admins)\nS-1-5-domain-512 (Domain Admins)\nS-1-5-114 (\"Local account and member of Administrators group\") or S-1-5-113 (\"Local account\")\n\nAll Systems:\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)\n\nNote: These are built-in security groups. \"Local account\" is more restrictive but may cause issues on servers such as systems that provide failover clustering.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny access to this computer from the network\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on from the network.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nLocal accounts on domain-joined systems must also be assigned this right to decrease the risk of lateral movement resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"3028","uuid":"6b6a9978-710c-458f-8007-0aa22957ca20","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: D31881E74FA9D285107EF72667AF4F1DC5312FE3\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Deny access to this computer from the network user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and local accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254436","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254436","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254436","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254436r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254436","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000090","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a batch job user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Deny log on as a batch job to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyBatchLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nS-1-5-root domain-519 (Enterprise Admins)\nS-1-5-domain-512 (Domain Admins)\n\nAll Systems:\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a batch job\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on to the system as a batch job, such as Task Scheduler.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"1474","uuid":"1ff9cc6b-d676-4a3b-9a0b-0039b5271a60","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 93E898A3CFA6996A7015D2B85E292D950ABCFD84\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a batch job user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254437","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254437","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254437","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254437r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254437","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000100","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a service user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts. No other groups or accounts must be assigned this right.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Deny log on as a service to include the following:\n\nDomain systems:\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on as a service\" user right on domain-joined systems, this is a finding:\n\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group\n\nIf any accounts or groups are defined for the \"Deny log on as a service\" user right on nondomain-joined systems, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyServiceLogonRight\" user right on domain-joined systems, this is a finding:\n\nS-1-5-root domain-519 (Enterprise Admins)\nS-1-5-domain-512 (Domain Admins)\n\nIf any SIDs are defined for the user right on nondomain-joined systems, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on as a service\" user right defines accounts that are denied logon as a service.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nIncorrect configurations could prevent services from starting and result in a denial of service.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"5501","uuid":"44b64110-c85c-4f6b-b52c-a90ed7f51f9e","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_applicable","overrides":{},"comments":"Not applicable - capability not installed/enabled on this asset.","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) marked this Not_Applicable on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 8521D5648CB76815E09E571D793E222988C368FA\r\n~~~~~\r\nThe feature/role addressed by 'Windows Server 2022 Deny log on as a service user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts. No other groups or accounts must be assigned this right.' is not present or not in use on this the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254438","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254438","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254438","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","rule_id_src":"SV-254438r1137691_rule","rule_id":"SV-254438","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000110","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on locally user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Deny log on locally to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests Group","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on locally\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins Group\n- Domain Admins Group\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests Group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nS-1-5-root domain-519 (Enterprise Admins)\nS-1-5-domain-512 (Domain Admins)\n\nAll Systems:\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on locally\" user right defines accounts that are prevented from logging on interactively.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000213"],"reference_identifier":"8467","uuid":"6029eb5e-91de-407f-929d-75de1c0998f5","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C4216F6DC576FAD9170C322B35E242614752B179\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Deny log on locally user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254439","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254439","title":"SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254439","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000297-GPOS-00115","rule_id_src":"SV-254439r958672_rule","rule_id":"SV-254439","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000120","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and all local accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services to include the following:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins group\n- Domain Admins group\n- Local account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests group\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is referring to the Windows built-in security group.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf the following accounts or groups are not defined for the \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right, this is a finding:\n\nDomain Systems Only:\n- Enterprise Admins group\n- Domain Admins group\n- Local account (see Note below)\n\nAll Systems:\n- Guests group\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf the following SIDs are not defined for the \"SeDenyRemoteInteractiveLogonRight\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nDomain Systems Only:\nS-1-5-root domain-519 (Enterprise Admins)\nS-1-5-domain-512 (Domain Admins)\nS-1-5-113 (\"Local account\")\n\nAll Systems:\nS-1-5-32-546 (Guests)\n\nNote: \"Local account\" is referring to the Windows built-in security group.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services\" user right defines the accounts that are prevented from logging on using Remote Desktop Services.\n\nIn an Active Directory Domain, denying logons to the Enterprise Admins and Domain Admins groups on lower-trust systems helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation from credential theft attacks, which could lead to the compromise of an entire domain.\n\nLocal accounts on domain-joined systems must also be assigned this right to decrease the risk of lateral movement resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nThe Guests group must be assigned this right to prevent unauthenticated access.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002314"],"reference_identifier":"3152","uuid":"e8a825ed-90ad-4f11-aa2d-277864d98b4b","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 40CA133ECA334CED6CD49957A5B2F6C1204CD510\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 Deny log on through Remote Desktop Services user right on domain-joined member servers must be configured to prevent access from highly privileged domain accounts and all local accounts and from unauthenticated access on all systems.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254440","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254440","title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254440","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000324-GPOS-00125","rule_id_src":"SV-254440r958726_rule","rule_id":"SV-254440","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000130","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts on domain-joined member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment >> Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation to be defined but containing no entries (blank).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This applies to member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems. A separate version applies to domain controllers.\n\nVerify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> User Rights Assignment.\n\nIf any accounts or groups are granted the \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right, this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas User_Rights /cfg c:\\path\\filename.txt\n\nReview the text file.\n\nIf any SIDs are granted the \"SeEnableDelegationPrivilege\" user right, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Inappropriate granting of user rights can provide system, administrative, and other high-level capabilities.\n\nThe \"Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation\" user right allows the \"Trusted for Delegation\" setting to be changed. This could allow unauthorized users to impersonate other users.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002235"],"reference_identifier":"8983","uuid":"7e771410-debe-4312-bac4-09c4299b2b13","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7DF270F82BCDE33FB9A8F9028F671EC4222589D0\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Enable computer and user accounts to be trusted for delegation user right must not be assigned to any groups or accounts on domain-joined member servers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254441","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254441","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254441","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254441r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254441","rule_version":"WN22-MS-000140","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be running Credential Guard on domain-joined member servers.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Administrative Templates >> System >> Device Guard >> Turn On Virtualization Based Security to \"Enabled\" with \"Enabled with UEFI lock\" selected for \"Credential Guard Configuration\".\n\nA Microsoft article on Credential Guard system requirement can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/identity-protection/credential-guard/credential-guard-requirements\n\nSeverity Override Guidance: The AO can allow the severity override if they have reviewed the overall protection provided to the affected servers that are not capable of complying with the Credential Guard requirement. Items that must be reviewed/considered for compliance or mitigation for non-Credential Guard compliance are:\n\nThe use of Microsoft Local Administrator Password Solution (LAPS) or similar products to control different local administrative passwords for all affected servers. This is to include a strict password change requirement (60 days or less).\n....\nStrict separation of roles and duties. Server administrator credentials cannot be used on Windows 10 desktop to administer it. Documentation of all exceptions must be supplied.\n....\nUse of a Privileged Access Workstation (PAW) and adherence to the Clean Source principle for administering affected servers. \n....\nBoundary Protection that is currently in place to protect from vulnerabilities in the network/servers.\n....\nWindows Defender rule block credential stealing from LSASS.exe is applied. This rule can only be applied if Windows Defender is in use.\n....\nThe overall number of vulnerabilities that are unmitigated on the network/servers.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"For domain controllers and standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\n\n\"Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32_DeviceGuard -Namespace root\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\"\n\nIf \"SecurityServicesRunning\" does not include a value of \"1\" (e.g., \"{1, 2}\"), this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", verify the following:\n\nIf \"Device Guard Security Services Running\" does not list \"Credential Guard\", this is a finding.\n\nThe policy settings referenced in the Fix section will configure the following registry value. However, due to hardware requirements, the registry value alone does not ensure proper function.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\DeviceGuard\\\n\nValue Name: LsaCfgFlags\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1) (Enabled with UEFI lock)\n\nA Microsoft article on Credential Guard system requirement can be found at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/identity-protection/credential-guard/credential-guard-requirements","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Credential Guard uses virtualization-based security to protect data that could be used in credential theft attacks if compromised. This authentication information, which was stored in the Local Security Authority (LSA) in previous versions of Windows, is isolated from the rest of operating system and can only be accessed by privileged system software.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3331","uuid":"5e802b6f-c607-4515-bed9-33f5e3ffc381","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: F7D4422ADBF122BCF04E00E2F21A7C338B673453\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be running Credential Guard on domain-joined member servers.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254442","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254442","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254442","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-254442r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-254442","rule_version":"WN22-PK-000010","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the DoD Root Certificate Authority (CA) certificates installed in the Trusted Root Store.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Root CA certificates:\n\nDoD Root CA 3\nDoD Root CA 4\nDoD Root CA 5\nDoD Root CA 6\n\nThe InstallRoot tool is available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. Certificate bundles published by the PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"The certificates and thumbprints referenced below apply to unclassified systems; refer to PKE documentation for other networks.\n\nOpen \"Windows PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\root | Where Subject -Like \"*DoD*\" | FL Subject, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\" and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nNotAfter: 12/30/2029\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 4, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nNotAfter: 7/25/2032\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 5, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nNotAfter: 6/14/2041\n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 6, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US \nThumbprint : D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEF\nNotAfter: 1/24/2053 11:36:17 AM\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\" and click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\" and click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\" and click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to \"Trusted Root Certification Authorities >> Certificates\".\n\nFor each of the DoD Root CA certificates noted below:\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the DoD Root CA certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nDoD Root CA 3\nThumbprint: D73CA91102A2204A36459ED32213B467D7CE97FB\nValid to: Sunday, December 30, 2029\n\nDoD Root CA 4\nThumbprint: B8269F25DBD937ECAFD4C35A9838571723F2D026\nValid to: Sunday, July 25, 2032\n\nDoD Root CA 5\nThumbprint: 4ECB5CC3095670454DA1CBD410FC921F46B8564B\nValid to: Friday, June 14, 2041\n\nDoD Root CA 6\nThumbprint: D37ECF61C0B4ED88681EF3630C4E2FC787B37AEFB\nValid to: Friday, January 24, 2053","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure secure DoD websites and DoD-signed code are properly validated, the system must trust the DoD Root CAs. The DoD root certificates will ensure that the trust chain is established for server certificates issued from the DoD CAs.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034, SRG-OS-000403-GPOS-00182","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"7586","uuid":"957f2059-b63d-48d4-9130-ab8d6f0fb5af","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2B9640E9115C166501BF8361206B197DF07546F8\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 must have the DoD Root Certificate Authority (CA) certificates installed in the Trusted Root Store.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254443","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254443","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254443","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-254443r958448_rule","rule_id":"SV-254443","rule_version":"WN22-PK-000020","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the DoD Interoperability Root Certificate Authority (CA) cross-certificates installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\n\nDoD Root CA 3- DoD Interoperability Root CA 2 - 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\n\nAdministrators must run the Federal Bridge Certification Authority (FBCA) Cross-Certificate Removal Tool once as an administrator and once as the current user.\n\nThe FBCA Cross-Certificate Remover Tool and User Guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. Certificate bundles published by the PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. It is NA for others.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where {$_.Issuer -Like \"*DoD Interoperability*\" -and $_.Subject -Like \"*DoD*\"} | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding. \n\nSubject: CN=DoD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=DoD Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DoD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nNotAfter: 11/16/2024 09:57:16 AM\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\" and click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\" and click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\" and click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"DoD Root CA...\" under \"Issued To\" and \"DoD Interoperability Root CA...\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificates below are not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nIssued To: DoD Root CA 3\nIssued By: DoD Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint: 49CBE933151872E17C8EAE7F0ABA97FB610F6477\nValid to: Wednesday, November 16, 2024","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DoD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DoD Root CAs, the DoD Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034, SRG-OS-000403-GPOS-00182","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"8249","uuid":"156ffd37-4190-4f7d-93ad-4ff39e94413b","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A78F7FFC99B5FF5AA5759D5E9792CF156625137F\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must have the DoD Interoperability Root Certificate Authority (CA) cross-certificates installed in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254444","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254444","title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254444","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034","rule_id_src":"SV-254444r1081077_rule","rule_id":"SV-254444","rule_version":"WN22-PK-000030","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.","fix_text":"Install the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificate on unclassified systems.\n\nIssued To - Issued By - Thumbprint\n\nDOD Root CA 3 - US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2 - 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8 \nDOD Root CA 6 -US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2 - D471CA32F7A692CE6CBB6196BD3377FE4DBCD106\n\nAdministrators must run the Federal Bridge Certification Authority (FBCA) Cross-Certificate Removal Tool once as an administrator and once as the current user.\n\nThe FBCA Cross-Certificate Remover Tool and User Guide are available on Cyber Exchange at https://cyber.mil/pki-pke/tools-configuration-files. PKI can be found at https://crl.gds.disa.mil/.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is applicable to unclassified systems. It is NA for others.\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\" as an administrator.\n\nExecute the following command:\n\nGet-ChildItem -Path Cert:Localmachine\\disallowed | Where Issuer -Like \"*CCEB Interoperability*\" | FL Subject, Issuer, Thumbprint, NotAfter\n\nIf the following certificate \"Subject\", \"Issuer\", and \"Thumbprint\" information is not displayed, this is a finding.\n\nSubject: CN=DOD Root CA 3, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nIssuer: CN=US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2, OU=PKI, OU=DOD, O=U.S. Government, C=US\nThumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025 9:56:22 AM\n\nAlternately, use the Certificates MMC snap-in:\n\nRun \"MMC\".\n\nSelect \"File\", \"Add/Remove Snap-in\".\n\nSelect \"Certificates\" and click \"Add\".\n\nSelect \"Computer account\" and click \"Next\".\n\nSelect \"Local computer: (the computer this console is running on)\" and click \"Finish\".\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nExpand \"Certificates\" and navigate to Untrusted Certificates >> Certificates.\n\nFor each certificate with \"US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA ...\" under \"Issued By\":\n\nRight-click on the certificate and select \"Open\".\n\nSelect the \"Details\" tab.\n\nScroll to the bottom and select \"Thumbprint\".\n\nIf the certificate below is not listed or the value for the \"Thumbprint\" field is not as noted, this is a finding.\n\nIssued To: DOD Root CA 3\nIssued By: US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint: 9B74964506C7ED9138070D08D5F8B969866560C8\nNotAfter: 7/18/2025\nIssued to: DOD Root CA 6\nIssued By: US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA 2\nThumbprint: D471CA32F7A692CE6CBB6196BD3377FE4DBCD106\nNotAfter: 7/18/2026","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"To ensure users do not experience denial of service when performing certificate-based authentication to DOD websites due to the system chaining to a root other than DOD Root CAs, the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates must be installed in the Untrusted Certificate Store. This requirement only applies to unclassified systems.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000066-GPOS-00034, SRG-OS-000403-GPOS-00182","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000185","CCI-002470"],"reference_identifier":"2952","uuid":"93f15a1f-b9b7-40f5-9670-2c113143df0e","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 2354C5D38EA2460650D15484AF488090A3547CDF\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must have the US DOD CCEB Interoperability Root CA cross-certificates in the Untrusted Certificates Store on unclassified systems.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254445","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254445","title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254445","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","rule_id_src":"SV-254445r958504_rule","rule_id":"SV-254445","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000010","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must have the built-in guest account disabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Accounts: Guest account status to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Guest account status\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"EnableGuestAccount\" equals \"1\" in the file, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A system faces an increased vulnerability threat if the built-in guest account is not disabled. This is a known account that exists on all Windows systems and cannot be deleted. This account is initialized during the installation of the operating system with no password assigned.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000804"],"reference_identifier":"8409","uuid":"bca48a5f-f6c7-498c-a7e0-c5983093f4b3","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 7E70F01D3E0B54582F9A88B015A5490D6DC09290\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must have the built-in guest account disabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254446","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254446","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254446","severity":"high","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254446r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254446","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000020","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must prevent local accounts with blank passwords from being used from the network.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Accounts: Limit local account use of blank passwords to console logon only to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: LimitBlankPasswordUse\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"An account without a password can allow unauthorized access to a system as only the username would be required. Password policies must prevent accounts with blank passwords from existing on a system. However, if a local account with a blank password does exist, enabling this setting will prevent network access, limiting the account to local console logon only.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1360","uuid":"df0416bc-4292-40a8-9050-3e128d94e1b8","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: C62BB99F9A956B312AAF96CAB00498A1F3B8A519\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must prevent local accounts with blank passwords from being used from the network.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254447","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254447","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254447","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254447r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254447","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000030","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 built-in administrator account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Accounts: Rename administrator account to a name other than \"Administrator\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename administrator account\" is not set to a value other than \"Administrator\", this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"NewAdministratorName\" is not something other than \"Administrator\" in the file, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in administrator account is a well-known account subject to attack. Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"1277","uuid":"4a1a4437-8fee-460e-8def-4c029fc23aa8","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 9BDF30B8EB6CF81351C03D367275E3172D66A7A5\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 built-in administrator account must be renamed.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254448","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254448","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254448","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254448r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254448","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000040","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 built-in guest account must be renamed.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Accounts: Rename guest account to a name other than \"Guest\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\n\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy >> Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options.\n\nIf the value for \"Accounts: Rename guest account\" is not set to a value other than \"Guest\", this is a finding.\n\nFor server core installations, run the following command:\n\nSecedit /Export /Areas SecurityPolicy /CFG C:\\Path\\FileName.Txt\n\nIf \"NewGuestName\" is not something other than \"Guest\" in the file, this is a finding.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The built-in guest account is a well-known user account on all Windows systems and, as initially installed, does not require a password. This can allow access to system resources by unauthorized users. Renaming this account to an unidentified name improves the protection of this account and the system.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"3275","uuid":"d51aa161-c3b1-451b-bafb-078ab0c23e91","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E73DC0DCB9DED9ECCC5748F162516EFDCA59A536\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 built-in guest account must be renamed.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254449","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254449","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254449","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","rule_id_src":"SV-254449r958442_rule","rule_id":"SV-254449","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000050","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Lsa\\\n\nValue Name: SCENoApplyLegacyAuditPolicy\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. This setting allows administrators to enable more precise auditing capabilities.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"reference_identifier":"8560","uuid":"67d150dc-4067-4ad1-bfd3-a2bd87d59de3","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DCF05681AFBB4AD0F0F443BEED41A3425F16C4DE\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254450","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254450","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254450","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-254450r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-254450","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000060","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Domain member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always) must be configured to Enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Domain member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always) to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSignOrSeal\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted. If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted and signed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"8461","uuid":"18846546-eaef-4301-85f4-aa19bc8f3a4a","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 33E8480668F2944C004DC54A3DFF159FC1433906\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 setting Domain member: Digitally encrypt or sign secure channel data (always) must be configured to Enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254451","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254451","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254451","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-254451r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-254451","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000070","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Domain member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible) must be configured to Enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Domain member: Digitally encrypt secure channel data (when possible) to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SealSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but not all information is encrypted. If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be encrypted.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"6001","uuid":"c91f9cbe-0704-478e-b56c-318aa235c442","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"not_reviewed","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":""},{"group_id_src":"V-254452","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254452","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254452","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-254452r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-254452","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000080","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Domain member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible) must be configured to Enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Domain member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible) to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SignSecureChannel\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Requests sent on the secure channel are authenticated, and sensitive information (such as passwords) is encrypted, but the channel is not integrity checked. If this policy is enabled, outgoing secure channel traffic will be signed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"5772","uuid":"7a729085-ff89-4f80-866e-b03040d952b6","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: DAD4E15DC25DD5AA7F5CFC99443A6AE40F06822B\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 setting Domain member: Digitally sign secure channel data (when possible) must be configured to Enabled.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254453","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254453","title":"SRG-OS-000379-GPOS-00164","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254453","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000379-GPOS-00164","rule_id_src":"SV-254453r971545_rule","rule_id":"SV-254453","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000090","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 computer account password must not be prevented from being reset.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Domain member: Disable machine account password changes to \"Disabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: DisablePasswordChange\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis. Disabling automatic password changes can make the system more vulnerable to malicious access. Frequent password changes can be a significant safeguard for the system. A new password for the computer account will be generated every 30 days.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-001967"],"reference_identifier":"6745","uuid":"55161f17-6e9a-4d38-b352-ca64dc2c1618","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 4586713E49E07C8A55C43D9EF5B53353F9A60B5F\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 computer account password must not be prevented from being reset.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254454","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254454","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254454","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254454r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254454","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000100","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 maximum age for machine account passwords must be configured to 30 days or less.","fix_text":"This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Domain member: Maximum machine account password age to \"30\" or less (excluding \"0\", which is unacceptable).","weight":"10.0","check_content":"This is the default configuration for this setting (30 days).\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: MaximumPasswordAge\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x0000001e (30) (or less, but not 0)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Computer account passwords are changed automatically on a regular basis. This setting controls the maximum password age that a machine account may have. This must be set to no more than 30 days, ensuring the machine changes its password monthly.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"9211","uuid":"45df9021-9c5a-4ace-9138-5405668c045c","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 5F8A613038AF3A5396A4627F6D1651003813F2AB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 maximum age for machine account passwords must be configured to 30 days or less.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254455","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254455","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254455","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-254455r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-254455","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000110","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 must be configured to require a strong session key.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Domain member: Require strong (Windows 2000 or Later) session key to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\Netlogon\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireStrongKey\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n \nThis setting may prevent a system from being joined to a domain if not configured consistently between systems.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"A computer connecting to a domain controller will establish a secure channel. The secure channel connection may be subject to compromise, such as hijacking or eavesdropping, if strong session keys are not used to establish the connection. Requiring strong session keys enforces 128-bit encryption between systems.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"1409","uuid":"45ae19ae-0ef5-4ff4-87fc-1240aadc651a","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E5E2628FD8CACD5187CC79B4FCC14B488685A3DB\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 must be configured to require a strong session key.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254456","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254456","title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254456","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009","rule_id_src":"SV-254456r958400_rule","rule_id":"SV-254456","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000120","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 machine inactivity limit must be set to 15 minutes or less, locking the system with the screen saver.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Interactive logon: Machine inactivity limit to \"900\" seconds or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: InactivityTimeoutSecs\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000384 (900) (or less, excluding \"0\" which is effectively disabled)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked when unattended. The screen saver must be set at a maximum of 15 minutes and be password protected. This protects critical and sensitive data from exposure to unauthorized personnel with physical access to the computer.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000028-GPOS-00009, SRG-OS-000029-GPOS-00010, SRG-OS-000031-GPOS-00012","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000056","CCI-000057","CCI-000060"],"reference_identifier":"9978","uuid":"9c8df1f3-9c4c-4f54-9f16-7e67a7d784a8","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: A29DAE0566F01AECD19EE1272401141B1FD91B88\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 machine inactivity limit must be set to 15 minutes or less, locking the system with the screen saver.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254457","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254457","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254457","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","rule_id_src":"SV-254457r958390_rule","rule_id":"SV-254457","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000130","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Interactive Logon: Message text for users attempting to log on to the following:\n\nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants. Such communications and work product are private and confidential. See User Agreement for details.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeText\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: See message text below\n\nYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only.\n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions:\n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations.\n\n-At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS.\n\n-Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose.\n\n-This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interests--not for your personal benefit or privacy.\n\n-Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants. Such communications and work product are private and confidential. See User Agreement for details.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006, SRG-OS-000024-GPOS-00007, SRG-OS-000228-GPOS-00088","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000048","CCI-000050","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"9263","uuid":"a2f3b05c-44e4-47f2-a089-eaae7fd157a9","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: 649B97B0648596D958D1D40F1E806334414B846B\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 required legal notice must be configured to display before console logon.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254458","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254458","title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254458","severity":"low","group_title":"SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006","rule_id_src":"SV-254458r958390_rule","rule_id":"SV-254458","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000140","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 title for legal banner dialog box must be configured with the appropriate text.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Interactive Logon: Message title for users attempting to log on to \"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\", or an organization-defined equivalent. \n\nIf an organization-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the message text required in WN22-SO-000150.","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\System\\\n\nValue Name: LegalNoticeCaption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: See message title options below\n\n\"DoD Notice and Consent Banner\", \"US Department of Defense Warning Statement\", or an organization-defined equivalent. \n\nIf an organization-defined title is used, it can in no case contravene or modify the language of the banner text required in WN22-SO-000150.\n\nAutomated tools may only search for the titles defined above. If an organization-defined title is used, a manual review will be required.","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Failure to display the logon banner prior to a logon attempt will negate legal proceedings resulting from unauthorized access to system resources.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000023-GPOS-00006, SRG-OS-000228-GPOS-00088","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000048","CCI-001384","CCI-001385","CCI-001386","CCI-001387","CCI-001388"],"reference_identifier":"2626","uuid":"f6d8c2fd-5b4c-4f5a-acff-1f0ea129c277","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"notafinding","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be NotAFinding on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: FE64ED5306BA2EA82B772FF4C28CA798537CBCCB\r\n~~~~~\r\nConfiguration for 'Windows Server 2022 title for legal banner dialog box must be configured with the appropriate text.' matches the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254459","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254459","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254459","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","rule_id_src":"SV-254459r991589_rule","rule_id":"SV-254459","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000150","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Interactive logon: Smart card removal behavior to \"Lock Workstation\" or \"Force Logoff\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows NT\\CurrentVersion\\Winlogon\\\n \nValue Name: scremoveoption\n\nValue Type: REG_SZ\nValue: 1 (Lock Workstation) or 2 (Force Logoff)\n\nIf configuring this on servers causes issues, such as terminating users' remote sessions, and the organization has a policy in place that any other sessions on the servers, such as administrative console logons, are manually locked or logged off when unattended or not in use, this would be acceptable. This must be documented with the Information System Security Officer (ISSO).","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"Unattended systems are susceptible to unauthorized use and must be locked. Configuring a system to lock when a smart card is removed will ensure the system is inaccessible when unattended.","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"reference_identifier":"2160","uuid":"9be9cb41-4c12-46af-93e7-7122238e8c68","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: B1D8E3788DCAA66D7492470AAE6411DBBD9C09D4\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 Smart Card removal option must be configured to Force Logoff or Lock Workstation.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254460","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254460","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254460","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-254460r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-254460","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000160","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (always) must be configured to Enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (always) to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: RequireSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations. Digitally signed SMB packets aid in preventing man-in-the-middle attacks. If this policy is enabled, the SMB client will only communicate with an SMB server that performs SMB packet signing.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"],"reference_identifier":"9779","uuid":"5962a8a9-b42c-4aa9-af30-0eb39bd1366a","stig_uuid":"63ad97ff-f4d5-48c7-b3af-f56a9540c49d","status":"open","overrides":{},"comments":"","finding_details":"Evaluate-STIG 1.2604.2 (Scan-WindowsServer2022_Checks) found this to be OPEN on 07/23/2026\r\nResultHash: E9C04776DCCC727209FC4716F04877FDAEDB1325\r\n~~~~~\r\nRequired configuration for 'Windows Server 2022 setting Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (always) must be configured to Enabled.' was not present or did not match the expected value on the Windows Server 2022 host."},{"group_id_src":"V-254461","group_tree":[{"id":"V-254461","title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","description":"<GroupDescription></GroupDescription>"}],"group_id":"V-254461","severity":"medium","group_title":"SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187","rule_id_src":"SV-254461r958908_rule","rule_id":"SV-254461","rule_version":"WN22-SO-000170","rule_title":"Windows Server 2022 setting Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (if server agrees) must be configured to Enabled.","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration >> Windows Settings >> Security Settings >> Local Policies >> Security Options >> Microsoft network client: Digitally sign communications (if server agrees) to \"Enabled\".","weight":"10.0","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE \nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanWorkstation\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: EnableSecuritySignature\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)","check_content_ref":{"href":"Microsoft_Windows_Server_2022_STIG.xml","name":"M"},"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","discussion":"The server message block (SMB) protocol provides the basis for many network operations. If this policy is enabled, the SMB client will request packet signing when communicating with an SMB server that is enabled or required to perform SMB packet signing.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000423-GPOS-00187, SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","false_positives":"","false_negatives":"","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","potential_impacts":"","third_party_tools":"","ia_controls":"","responsibility":"","mitigations":"","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"ccis":["CCI-002418","CCI-002421"]